MR. KLEIN? YOU'VE BEEN HIT
BY A CAR. IT IS IMPORTANT --

7
00:01:20,778 --> 00:01:22,980
I WOULDN'T
RECOMMEND THAT --
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

8
00:01:23,047 --> 00:01:25,149
WHERE'S JENNY? LISTEN TO ME.
YOU -- YOU WERE IN
A CAR ACCIDENT.

9
00:01:25,216 --> 00:01:26,617
LISTEN TO ME --
YOU'VE BEEN HIT BY A CAR.

10
00:01:26,684 --> 00:01:27,785
JENNY!!

11
00:01:27,852 --> 00:01:29,754
YOU HAVE TO FIND JENNY.
SHE --
JENNY!

12
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:30,988
IT IS IMPORTANT
FOR YOU TO STAY --

13
00:01:31,055 --> 00:01:32,623
LET ME OUT
OF THIS THING!

14
00:01:32,690 --> 00:01:33,891
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

15
00:01:33,958 --> 00:01:35,693
AH!

16
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:36,994
[ HORN HONKING ]
PLEASE!

17
00:01:37,061 --> 00:01:38,796
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

18
00:01:38,863 --> 00:01:39,997
A-AH!

19
00:01:40,064 --> 00:01:41,299
AH!

20
00:01:41,365 --> 00:01:42,700
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS
CONTINUE ]

21
00:01:44,335 --> 00:01:45,937
[ BEEPING ]
[ Echoing ] MR. KLEIN?

22
00:01:46,003 --> 00:01:47,305
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

23
00:01:47,371 --> 00:01:49,607
MR. KLEIN?

24
00:01:49,674 --> 00:01:50,441
AH.

25
00:01:50,508 --> 00:01:51,943
I'M DETECTIVE ANDERS.

26
00:01:52,009 --> 00:01:53,945
THIS IS DETECTIVE NAGLE.

27
00:01:54,011 --> 00:01:55,246
[ GASPS ]

28
00:01:55,313 --> 00:01:57,848
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]
WE'RE HERE TO HELP.

29
00:01:57,915 --> 00:02:00,985
BUT WE'RE GONNA NEED YOU TO
TELL US EXACTLY WHAT HAPPENED.

30
00:02:01,052 --> 00:02:02,987
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ON P.A. ]

31
00:02:05,056 --> 00:02:06,891
MR. KLEIN?
YEAH, YEAH.

32
00:02:06,958 --> 00:02:08,793
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

33
00:02:12,496 --> 00:02:14,732
HOW DOES HE EXPLAIN THESE?

34
00:02:18,002 --> 00:02:20,204
WHO'S JENNY, MR. KLEIN?

35
00:02:20,271 --> 00:02:22,406
[ INTENSE MUSIC PLAYS ]

36
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:27,745
SHE'S MY GIRLFRIEND.
I DON'T --

37
00:02:27,812 --> 00:02:29,947
CAN YOU TELL US
WHAT HAPPENED?

38
00:02:32,650 --> 00:02:35,019
DID YOU TWO HAVE A FIGHT,
SOMEBODY GET HURT?

39
00:02:38,756 --> 00:02:40,024
MR. KLEIN?

40
00:02:42,226 --> 00:02:43,628
MR. KLEIN?

41
00:02:45,229 --> 00:02:46,530
UM...

42
00:02:46,597 --> 00:02:48,899
SORRY, MY HEAD'S JUST...

43
00:02:50,301 --> 00:02:52,536
[ SIGHS ]

44
00:02:52,603 --> 00:02:56,407
I'M TRYING TO
REMEMBER, BUT...I CAN'T.

45
00:02:56,474 --> 00:02:58,743
MAYBE WE COULD START
WITH SOMETHING SIMPLE.

46
00:03:00,011 --> 00:03:01,879
START WITH YESTERDAY.

47
00:03:01,946 --> 00:03:04,782
DO YOU REMEMBER WHAT TIME
YOU GOT UP YESTERDAY?

48
00:03:04,849 --> 00:03:06,917
YEAH. YESTERDAY.

49
00:03:06,984 --> 00:03:08,886
[ GUNSHOT, JENNY SCREAMS,
GLASS BREAKS ]

50
00:03:08,953 --> 00:03:12,089
[ WOMAN MOANING, MATTRESS
CREAKING IN DISTANCE ]

51
00:03:31,242 --> 00:03:33,611
NO, JEN, WHERE YOU GOING?

52
00:03:35,446 --> 00:03:37,081
[ MOANS ]

53
00:03:41,619 --> 00:03:43,554
[ PILL BOTTLE RATTLING ]

54
00:03:45,556 --> 00:03:49,226
[ CLATTERING, FOOD SIZZLING ]

55
00:03:49,293 --> 00:03:51,062
WHERE ARE MY CIGARETTES?

56
00:03:51,128 --> 00:03:53,664
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

57
00:03:55,566 --> 00:03:57,501
[ BEEPS ]
HELLO?

58
00:03:59,003 --> 00:04:00,504
HELLO?!

59
00:04:00,571 --> 00:04:01,972
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

60
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:04,075
Buon giorno.

61
00:04:04,141 --> 00:04:05,910
Shalom.

62
00:04:07,445 --> 00:04:08,579
[ BEEPS ]

63
00:04:08,646 --> 00:04:10,715
[ Dial tone ]

64
00:04:10,781 --> 00:04:12,249
I'M LOSING MY MIND.
MY MIND IS LOST.

65
00:04:12,316 --> 00:04:13,984
ARE THEY IN HERE? NO.
HERE.

66
00:04:14,051 --> 00:04:16,487
TASTE THIS, TELL ME WHAT IT
NEEDS. I PUT A NEW INGREDIENT
IN THERE,

67
00:04:16,554 --> 00:04:18,389
SO I THOUGHT MAYBE --
SEE IF YOU COULD
FIGURE OUT WHAT IT --

68
00:04:18,456 --> 00:04:21,025
THERE ARE CIGARETTES
IN THIS HOUSE.
THEY SHOULD BE HERE.

69
00:04:21,092 --> 00:04:23,394
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING
IN DISTANCE ]

70
00:04:24,462 --> 00:04:25,996
HEY, WHAT'S THE
MATTER WITH YOU?

71
00:04:26,063 --> 00:04:27,832
YOU SHOULDN'T BE SMOKING
ANOTHER PACK ANYWAY.

72
00:04:27,898 --> 00:04:29,734
YOUR HEAD IS GONNA EXPLODE!

73
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,769
CAN WE PLEASE NOT DO THIS
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING?

74
00:04:31,836 --> 00:04:33,104
DO WHAT FIRST THING
IN THE MORNING?

75
00:04:33,170 --> 00:04:36,507
JUST DON'T BE THAT GUY,
DAVID, ALL RIGHT?

76
00:04:36,574 --> 00:04:38,576
WHAT GUY? I'M TRYING
TO MAKE YOU BREAKFAST.

77
00:04:38,642 --> 00:04:40,077
WHAT THE FUCK IS
WRONG WITH THAT?!

78
00:04:40,144 --> 00:04:43,047
NOTHING, ALL RIGHT, JUST,
WHERE ARE MY CIGARETTES?!

79
00:04:43,114 --> 00:04:46,350
[ GROANS ]

80
00:04:46,417 --> 00:04:47,818
UNH!

81
00:04:49,987 --> 00:04:51,822
[ SIGHS ] LOOKING
FOR THESE?

82
00:04:58,929 --> 00:05:01,499
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

83
00:05:05,469 --> 00:05:06,904
[ HORN HONKS IN DISTANCE ]

84
00:05:06,971 --> 00:05:08,506
DAVID...

85
00:05:10,007 --> 00:05:13,110
LOOK, DAVID...I'M SORRY,
ALL RIGHT?

86
00:05:13,177 --> 00:05:14,712
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

87
00:05:15,646 --> 00:05:16,680
[ UTENSILS CLATTERING ]

88
00:05:16,747 --> 00:05:18,382
I'M GONNA GO TAKE A WALK.

89
00:05:18,449 --> 00:05:21,085
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

90
00:05:28,425 --> 00:05:30,494
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

91
00:05:34,632 --> 00:05:36,200
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

92
00:05:43,474 --> 00:05:46,010
[ WATER RUNNING ]

93
00:05:50,247 --> 00:05:52,149
[ DOOR HINGES SQUEAK ]

94
00:05:52,216 --> 00:05:53,884
[ MAN SIGHS ]

95
00:05:56,654 --> 00:05:58,155
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

96
00:05:58,222 --> 00:06:00,925
[ DOOR OPENS, POUNDING ]

97
00:06:00,991 --> 00:06:02,126
DAVID?

98
00:06:04,895 --> 00:06:05,830
DAVID?

99
00:06:05,896 --> 00:06:07,631
[ POUNDING CONTINUES ]

100
00:06:08,966 --> 00:06:10,100
DAVID?

101
00:06:19,877 --> 00:06:21,011
DAVID?

102
00:06:21,078 --> 00:06:24,615
[ SCREECHES ]

103
00:06:24,682 --> 00:06:25,983
FUCKING CAT.

104
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:27,952
[ MEOWS ]
[ SIGHS ANGRILY ]

105
00:06:31,255 --> 00:06:33,524
[ WATER DRIPPING ]

106
00:06:39,463 --> 00:06:41,031
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

107
00:06:43,934 --> 00:06:46,136
DAVID?

108
00:06:46,203 --> 00:06:49,506
I THINK THEY GAVE THE
CORNER-STORE DOG A FLEA BATH.

109
00:06:49,573 --> 00:06:51,208
DAVID! [ GASPS ]

110
00:06:52,309 --> 00:06:53,410
AH!

111
00:06:53,477 --> 00:06:54,979
UNH!
AH!

112
00:06:55,045 --> 00:06:58,048
UNH! UGH!

113
00:06:58,115 --> 00:07:00,951
UNH!
AH!

114
00:07:01,018 --> 00:07:02,720
[ PANTING ]

115
00:07:04,655 --> 00:07:06,590
[ RUSTLING ]

116
00:07:08,525 --> 00:07:10,060
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

117
00:07:10,127 --> 00:07:11,428
[ WATER DRIPPING ]

118
00:07:11,495 --> 00:07:13,597
[ CHOKING ]
[ PANTING ]

119
00:07:13,664 --> 00:07:15,132
[ GUNSHOT ]
JENNY!

120
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:16,500
[ PANTING ]

121
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:18,035
[ GROANING ]

122
00:07:22,039 --> 00:07:23,173
UNH!

123
00:07:24,642 --> 00:07:26,644
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

124
00:07:32,249 --> 00:07:33,651
JENNY?

125
00:07:36,186 --> 00:07:38,088
ALAN?

126
00:07:38,155 --> 00:07:41,859
THE GUY WHO KIDNAPPED
YOU -- YOU KNOW HIM?

127
00:07:41,926 --> 00:07:43,227
YEAH.

128
00:07:43,294 --> 00:07:45,596
HIS NAME IS ALAN HAMMOND.

129
00:07:47,164 --> 00:07:49,199
OKAY, GET ON THE
PHONE TO WESTPORT.

130
00:07:49,266 --> 00:07:51,235
TELL THEM THAT WE'VE
GOT A KIDNAPPING,

131
00:07:51,302 --> 00:07:55,639
[ ELEVATOR DINGS ]
A POSSIBLE HOSTAGE SITUATION,
MAYBE EVEN A HOMICIDE.

132
00:08:00,544 --> 00:08:02,246
SO...
[ ELEVATOR DINGS ]

133
00:08:02,313 --> 00:08:05,649
YOU AND MR. HAMMOND --
HOW DO YOU KNOW EACH OTHER?

134
00:08:05,716 --> 00:08:07,518
HE WENT TO COLLEGE
WITH JEN AND ME.

135
00:08:07,584 --> 00:08:11,622
AND WHAT EXACTLY WAS
YOUR RELATIONSHIP?

136
00:08:11,689 --> 00:08:15,059
IT'S, UH...IT'S COMPLICATED.

137
00:08:15,125 --> 00:08:17,761
[ BELL TOLLS ]

138
00:08:17,828 --> 00:08:21,298
JEN AND I MET IN AN ENGLISH
SEMINAR JUNIOR YEAR --

139
00:08:21,365 --> 00:08:23,801
MODERN AMERICAN POETRY.

140
00:08:23,867 --> 00:08:25,569
FOR MOST OF THE SEMESTER,
SHE WAS THE GIRL

141
00:08:25,636 --> 00:08:27,771
TWO SEATS
OVER WHO WAS ALWAYS LATE.

142
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,909
SOMETIME IN MAY, I GOT UP
THE COURAGE TO ENGAGE HER

143
00:08:31,976 --> 00:08:35,346
IN A DISCUSSION OF T.S. ELIOT'S
THEORY OF INTENTION,

144
00:08:35,412 --> 00:08:36,914
WHICH TURNED INTO
AN ARGUMENT

145
00:08:36,981 --> 00:08:39,550
THAT LASTED UNTIL
OUR SENIOR YEAR.

146
00:08:39,616 --> 00:08:40,951
Jenny: FEELING IS FIRST.

147
00:08:41,018 --> 00:08:42,152
NO, NO, NO.
MM-HMM.

148
00:08:42,219 --> 00:08:44,955
ALL THAT MATTERS IS THE ACT.
WHY?

149
00:08:45,022 --> 00:08:49,827
BECAUSE THE ACT IS THE
MANIFESTATION OF THE THOUGHT.

150
00:08:49,893 --> 00:08:53,464
OH.
THE -- THE INTENTION
IS JUST FUEL.

151
00:08:53,530 --> 00:08:58,168
YEAH, BUT, I MEAN, PEOPLE --
THEY WANT TO HELP YOU, RIGHT?

152
00:08:58,235 --> 00:09:00,804
T-THEY'LL GO TO
THE STORE FOR YOU,

153
00:09:00,871 --> 00:09:02,473
BUY YOU STUFF.

154
00:09:02,539 --> 00:09:04,708
THAT DOESN'T --

155
00:09:04,775 --> 00:09:06,710
WHEN PUSH COMES TO SHOVE,

156
00:09:06,777 --> 00:09:09,346
WHAT THEY REALLY WANT IS
TO SLEEP WITH YOUR SISTER.

157
00:09:09,413 --> 00:09:10,681
NO, I --

158
00:09:10,748 --> 00:09:11,949
NO, NO, NO, NO.

159
00:09:12,016 --> 00:09:14,118
DAVID, I AM RIGHT
ABOUT THIS.

160
00:09:14,184 --> 00:09:16,387
I AM -- I AM RIGHT. PEOPLE --
THEY MAY WANT TO HELP YOU,

161
00:09:16,453 --> 00:09:19,490
OR THEY MAY JUST WANT...
WHAT THEY WANT.

162
00:09:19,556 --> 00:09:20,824
[ SCOFFS ]

163
00:09:23,660 --> 00:09:25,195
[ SCOFFS ]
LOOK AT ME.

164
00:09:27,231 --> 00:09:28,365
WHAT?

165
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,135
LOOK ME IN THE EYE.

166
00:09:31,201 --> 00:09:35,005
THE ACTION IS
I'M LOOKING AT YOU, RIGHT?

167
00:09:35,072 --> 00:09:39,943
THE ACTION IS
I'M STARING INTO YOU.

168
00:09:40,010 --> 00:09:43,747
BUT WHAT'S REALLY
IMPORTANT IS...THE WHY.

169
00:09:45,149 --> 00:09:46,817
WHY AM I STARING AT YOU?

170
00:09:46,884 --> 00:09:48,719
I DON'T KNOW.

171
00:09:48,786 --> 00:09:50,721
WHAT DO I WANT?

172
00:09:52,723 --> 00:09:54,358
WHAT...

173
00:09:54,425 --> 00:09:56,760
WILL...I...

174
00:09:57,795 --> 00:10:00,798
DO...NEXT?

175
00:10:02,466 --> 00:10:04,134
OW!
[ GIGGLING ]

176
00:10:04,201 --> 00:10:07,938
[ Laughing ] SHIT!
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU
JUST BIT MY NOSE.

177
00:10:08,005 --> 00:10:09,740
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

178
00:10:09,807 --> 00:10:11,742
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

179
00:10:13,377 --> 00:10:15,579
[ VEHICLE APPROACHES ]

180
00:10:15,646 --> 00:10:19,783
[ BRAKES SQUEAL ]

181
00:10:19,850 --> 00:10:22,386
[ CAR DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

182
00:10:22,453 --> 00:10:26,390
SO THAT WAS PRETTY SWEET
WHEN I PINNED THAT GUY
AT THE END, EH?
YEAH.

183
00:10:26,457 --> 00:10:27,524
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

184
00:10:27,591 --> 00:10:30,527
AHH! YEAH. MMM.

185
00:10:37,534 --> 00:10:39,269
[ BEEPING ]

186
00:10:39,336 --> 00:10:41,705
I'VE GOT ANOTHER ONE THIS
FRIDAY IF YOU WANT TO GO.
[ Ringing ]

187
00:10:41,772 --> 00:10:45,843
FRIDAY.
YEAH.

188
00:10:45,909 --> 00:10:47,511
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

189
00:10:47,578 --> 00:10:49,113
I SHOULD GET THAT.

190
00:10:52,583 --> 00:10:53,984
BYE.

191
00:10:57,788 --> 00:11:00,858
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

192
00:11:00,924 --> 00:11:02,759
[ Sighs ] Thanks
for the save.

193
00:11:02,826 --> 00:11:04,361
THAT BAD, HUH?
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

194
00:11:04,428 --> 00:11:06,396
Nothing.
He was totally flat.

195
00:11:06,463 --> 00:11:08,265
YEAH, WELL...YOU SHOULD
HAVE GUESSED THAT

196
00:11:08,332 --> 00:11:10,200
WHEN HE INVITED YOU TO
HIS WRESTLING MATCH.

197
00:11:10,267 --> 00:11:15,539
I just thought it would have
been kinda cute or kinky.

198
00:11:15,606 --> 00:11:17,841
I don't know -- either would
have been fine, really.

199
00:11:17,908 --> 00:11:19,877
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

200
00:11:19,943 --> 00:11:23,447
SO, UM, YOU GOT A --
A PLAN TONIGHT?

201
00:11:23,514 --> 00:11:26,950
Bath, book, bed. You?

202
00:11:27,017 --> 00:11:29,419
WELL, I GOT A PAPER,
SO

203
00:11:29,486 --> 00:11:31,989
PROBABLY JUST GO
DOWN TO THE COFFEE
SHOP, FINISH IT.

204
00:11:50,307 --> 00:11:51,975
WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING AT?

205
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:54,244
NOTHING.

206
00:11:56,780 --> 00:11:58,248
What's your paper on?

207
00:12:00,918 --> 00:12:01,952
HUH?

208
00:12:02,019 --> 00:12:04,154
Your paper --
What's it on?

209
00:12:06,356 --> 00:12:07,491
[ Chuckles ]

210
00:12:07,558 --> 00:12:09,960
How about this --
What class is it for?

211
00:12:10,027 --> 00:12:11,995
NO CLUE.

212
00:12:12,062 --> 00:12:14,598
[ ZIPPER CLICKS ]

213
00:12:17,034 --> 00:12:18,569
I'll call you
tomorrow, David.

214
00:12:18,635 --> 00:12:20,003
W-WAIT, UH, JEN...

215
00:12:20,070 --> 00:12:21,371
DO YOU BELIEVE
THERE'S ONE PERSON?

216
00:12:21,438 --> 00:12:25,142
UM...YOU KNOW, ONE PERSON
FOR EVERYONE?

217
00:12:26,643 --> 00:12:28,111
Absolutely.

218
00:12:29,146 --> 00:12:32,849
I believe in destiny.

219
00:12:32,916 --> 00:12:35,352
I believe you just
see someone,

220
00:12:35,419 --> 00:12:39,022
and you know right away.
[ ZIPPER CLICKS ]

221
00:12:39,089 --> 00:12:40,924
The big green light
will go off,

222
00:12:40,991 --> 00:12:43,393
and...that's it.

223
00:12:44,761 --> 00:12:46,463
[ THUMP ]
They're the one.

224
00:12:46,530 --> 00:12:50,500
YEAH, YEAH, BUT, I MEAN,
WHAT IF YOU DON'T --

225
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:53,704
I MEAN, WHAT IF YOU
DON'T KNOW AT FIRST?
WHAT IF IT'S SOMEONE --

226
00:12:53,770 --> 00:12:57,207
LIKE A FRIEND -- AND
THEN...YOU KNOW, YOU --
YOU REALIZE IT LATER?

227
00:12:58,642 --> 00:13:01,011
There's a difference between
friends and lovers, David.

228
00:13:01,078 --> 00:13:02,913
[ CHUCKLES ]

229
00:13:06,483 --> 00:13:07,884
[ THUD ]

230
00:13:07,951 --> 00:13:09,219
FUCKING!

231
00:13:09,286 --> 00:13:12,656
[ BELL TOLLS,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

232
00:13:25,502 --> 00:13:27,504
[ SOFT ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]
Jenny: WHAT'S THIS?

233
00:13:27,571 --> 00:13:30,040
READ IT.

234
00:13:30,107 --> 00:13:33,577
KLEIN-O-RAMA?

235
00:13:33,644 --> 00:13:35,279
[ Laughing ] THIS IS A
CHANCE TO SEE A FAMILY

236
00:13:35,345 --> 00:13:37,214
MORE SCREWED UP
THAN YOURS.

237
00:13:38,482 --> 00:13:40,050
SLIM CHANCE.

238
00:13:40,117 --> 00:13:41,952
[ Chuckling ] NO.

239
00:13:42,019 --> 00:13:43,320
BUNCH OF WEIRDOS.

240
00:13:43,387 --> 00:13:44,521
IS THAT CORN?

241
00:13:44,588 --> 00:13:47,224
IT'S A POTATO --
A BAKED POTATO.
OH.

242
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:50,961
