MAKING ME CRAZY" PLAYS ]
MY UNCLE DOES THIS EVERY YEAR --
GETS EVERYONE TOGETHER --

243
00:13:51,028 --> 00:13:53,130
MY COUSINS, THEIR WIVES.
[ SNICKERS ]

244
00:13:53,196 --> 00:13:55,999
LOOK, JENNY, YOU
HAVE TO UNDERSTAND

245
00:13:56,066 --> 00:13:57,934
THIS IS NOT MY SIDE
OF THE FAMILY.

246
00:13:58,001 --> 00:14:01,004
HEY, DAVID!
OKAY?

247
00:14:01,071 --> 00:14:03,307
YOU MADE IT!
[ LAUGHS ]

248
00:14:03,373 --> 00:14:05,575
UNCLE FINCH, HOW ARE YOU?
HOW'S THE KNEE?

249
00:14:05,642 --> 00:14:09,713
OH...BIG TURNOUT THIS YEAR --
EVERYBODY'S HERE.

250
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:12,849
EVERYBODY, EVEN YOUR
FRIEND MADE IT.

251
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:14,051
HEY!

252
00:14:14,117 --> 00:14:16,119
WHAT FRIEND?

253
00:14:16,186 --> 00:14:19,456
[ MUSIC, CONVERSATIONS
CONTINUE ]

254
00:14:19,523 --> 00:14:21,458
EXCUSE ME.

255
00:14:22,893 --> 00:14:24,995
HOW ARE YOU, SPAZ?

256
00:14:25,062 --> 00:14:27,030
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
ARE YOU KIDDING?

257
00:14:27,097 --> 00:14:30,167
I'M ON THE OFFICIAL
INVITEE LIST.
♪ CH-CH CH-CH
CH-CH CH-CH ♪

258
00:14:30,233 --> 00:14:31,368
YOU REMEMBER
YOUR GREAT-AUNT?

259
00:14:31,435 --> 00:14:33,003
Nana: DAVID.
HELLO, NANA.

260
00:14:33,070 --> 00:14:35,038
FANCY A DIP?
OH...

261
00:14:35,105 --> 00:14:38,342
OOH!
[ CHUCKLES ]

262
00:14:38,408 --> 00:14:40,677
♪ MY FEET LEAVE THE GROUND,
AND I'M RUNNING AROUND ♪
SWITCH.

263
00:14:40,744 --> 00:14:42,112
♪ ON THE CEILING ♪

264
00:14:42,179 --> 00:14:44,247
[ CHUCKLING ]
♪ I'M FEELING SO HAZY ♪

265
00:14:44,314 --> 00:14:46,550
♪ SINCE YOU MADE ME CARE ♪

266
00:14:46,616 --> 00:14:49,886
♪ I'M TALKING TO THE FURNITURE
WHEN YOU'RE NOT THERE ♪

267
00:14:49,953 --> 00:14:52,889
♪ YOU'RE MAKING ME CRAZY,
CAN'T YOU SEE IT'S TRUE? ♪♪

268
00:14:52,956 --> 00:14:54,091
YOU'RE VERY GOOD,

269
00:14:54,157 --> 00:14:56,727
ESPECIALLY CONSIDERING
I CAN'T DANCE.

270
00:14:56,793 --> 00:14:58,729
IT'S A TRICK NANA TAUGHT ME.

271
00:14:58,795 --> 00:15:02,232
HOLD YOUR PARTNER
CLOSE ENOUGH SO YOU CAN
FEEL THEIR HEART BEAT.

272
00:15:02,299 --> 00:15:04,101
USE THAT AS YOUR GUIDE.

273
00:15:04,167 --> 00:15:05,769
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

274
00:15:07,204 --> 00:15:09,139
SMILE A LITTLE.

275
00:15:09,206 --> 00:15:11,241
[ Laughing ] OKAY.

276
00:15:12,809 --> 00:15:14,778
ALAN HAMMOND.

277
00:15:14,845 --> 00:15:16,146
JENNY KELLEY.

278
00:15:17,013 --> 00:15:18,949
WELL, HEY, JENNY.

279
00:15:19,016 --> 00:15:23,086
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

280
00:15:23,153 --> 00:15:25,188
SO, YOU GUYS USED
TO BE ROOMMATES?

281
00:15:25,255 --> 00:15:27,591
UH-HUH, FRESHMAN YEAR.
WE GOT ASSIGNED.

282
00:15:27,657 --> 00:15:31,361
ACTUALLY, WHAT YOU NEVER
KNEW WAS THAT I WAS BEING
PAID TO HANG OUT WITH YOU.

283
00:15:31,428 --> 00:15:32,863
I GOTTA TELL YOU, IF
IT WASN'T FOR THIS GUY,

284
00:15:32,929 --> 00:15:34,631
I WOULD HAVE BOMBED OUT
FIRST SEMESTER.

285
00:15:34,698 --> 00:15:37,968
[ Laughing ] MM-HMM.
INSTEAD, HE BOMBED
OUT SECOND SEMESTER.

286
00:15:38,035 --> 00:15:40,537
[ LAUGHTER ]
DAVID GOT ME THROUGH.

287
00:15:40,604 --> 00:15:42,305
YEAH, ALMOST KILLING ME
IN THE PROCESS.

288
00:15:42,372 --> 00:15:43,874
ALAN GOT ME ARRESTED.

289
00:15:43,940 --> 00:15:45,008
NOT MY FAULT.

290
00:15:45,075 --> 00:15:46,276
STREAKING.

291
00:15:46,343 --> 00:15:49,413
YEAH, ALAN HAS A THING
FOR STREAKING.

292
00:15:49,479 --> 00:15:51,114
NO, NO, NO,
HERE'S THE STORY.

293
00:15:51,181 --> 00:15:53,583
I CHALLENGED DAVID TO
A RACE DOWN MAIN STREET

294
00:15:53,650 --> 00:15:55,852
WEARING NOTHING
BUT COWBOY BOOTS. YEE-HAW!

295
00:15:55,919 --> 00:15:58,255
IT'S FRIDAY NIGHT,
AND THE STREETS ARE PACKED.

296
00:15:58,321 --> 00:15:59,689
AND WE'RE HALFWAY
DOWN THIS BLOCK

297
00:15:59,756 --> 00:16:03,160
OUTSIDE A BURRITO STAND OR
SOMETHING, AND DAVID TRIPS,

298
00:16:03,226 --> 00:16:04,761
TUMBLES OUT ONTO
THIS STREET,

299
00:16:04,828 --> 00:16:07,164
STOPPING TRAFFIC AND GETTING
PAVEMENT BURNS ON HIS ASS.

300
00:16:07,230 --> 00:16:08,899
ON MY KNEES, MY KNEES.

301
00:16:08,965 --> 00:16:10,667
[ LAUGHTER ]

302
00:16:10,734 --> 00:16:14,438
JUST DAVID'S LUCK,
OFFICER FRIENDLY STEPS
OUT OF THE BURRITO STAND,

303
00:16:14,504 --> 00:16:16,907
SEES DAVID, AND SLAPS
THE CUFFS ON HIM.

304
00:16:16,973 --> 00:16:20,010
I MEAN, THE COP WALKED
HIM FOUR BLOCKS WITH
HIS PACKAGE IN A NAPKIN.

305
00:16:20,076 --> 00:16:22,079
[ LAUGHTER ]

306
00:16:22,145 --> 00:16:25,449
OH! WHERE WERE YOU
IN ALL OF THIS?

307
00:16:25,515 --> 00:16:28,452
EXACTLY, EXACTLY, THAT'S
THE WHOLE POINT, JEN.

308
00:16:28,518 --> 00:16:31,154
HE LEFT ME -- HE
FUCKING LEFT ME.

309
00:16:31,221 --> 00:16:33,423
[ LAUGHING ]

310
00:16:35,425 --> 00:16:38,895
I'M COMING BACK...
TO SCHOOL.

311
00:16:38,962 --> 00:16:40,497
WHEN?

312
00:16:40,564 --> 00:16:42,399
NOW.

313
00:16:42,466 --> 00:16:46,837
NOW?! ALAN, CLASSES HAVE
BEEN GOING FOR THREE WEEKS.

314
00:16:46,903 --> 00:16:48,705
SO?

315
00:16:48,772 --> 00:16:50,240
[ CHUCKLES ]

316
00:16:50,307 --> 00:16:52,175
YOU'RE BACK.

317
00:16:52,242 --> 00:16:54,211
I'M BACK.

318
00:16:54,277 --> 00:16:56,346
GOD HELP US ALL.

319
00:16:56,413 --> 00:16:59,516
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

320
00:17:05,255 --> 00:17:06,723
HOW'S THAT FEEL?!

321
00:17:06,790 --> 00:17:07,824
PERFECT.

322
00:17:07,891 --> 00:17:09,559
ALL RIGHT, THIS HAS --
THIS HAS BEEN --

323
00:17:09,626 --> 00:17:11,328
UH, THIS HAS BEEN A BLAST,
BUT CAN YOU --

324
00:17:11,394 --> 00:17:13,997
CAN YOU PLEASE
PULL THE CAR OVER?

325
00:17:14,064 --> 00:17:15,298
TAKE THE WHEEL,
WILL YOU?

326
00:17:15,365 --> 00:17:17,667
WHAT? COME ON.

327
00:17:17,734 --> 00:17:19,302
ON THE COUNT OF THREE,
YOU'RE GONNA SLIDE OVER

328
00:17:19,369 --> 00:17:20,904
AND TAKE THE WHEEL, AND
I'M GOING OUT THE WINDOW.

329
00:17:20,971 --> 00:17:23,273
ALAN, NOT FUCKING
DOING THIS. 1...

330
00:17:23,340 --> 00:17:25,041
NO! ALAN!
2...

331
00:17:25,108 --> 00:17:26,276
STAY IN THE CAR!

332
00:17:26,343 --> 00:17:27,711
2 1/2...
ALAN, STAY IN THE CAR!

333
00:17:27,777 --> 00:17:30,280
3!
YOU -- AH, SHIT!
DON'T YOU...

334
00:17:30,347 --> 00:17:33,717
FUCKIN' DARE!
SHIT!

335
00:17:33,783 --> 00:17:34,784
WHOO-HOO!

336
00:17:34,851 --> 00:17:37,621
HAVE YOU COMPLETELY
LOST YOUR MIND?

337
00:17:37,687 --> 00:17:38,555
YES.

338
00:17:38,622 --> 00:17:40,390
YOU COULD HAVE
KILLED YOURSELF.

339
00:17:40,457 --> 00:17:42,292
NAH, I'M NOT DESTINED
TO DIE IN A CAR.

340
00:17:42,359 --> 00:17:44,294
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

341
00:17:44,361 --> 00:17:46,296
I BELIEVE IN ONLY
TWO THINGS --

342
00:17:46,363 --> 00:17:48,498
DESTINY...

343
00:17:48,565 --> 00:17:51,868
AND THE BEAUTY OF
THE IMPULSIVE ACT.

344
00:17:51,935 --> 00:17:54,004
WHOO!

345
00:17:54,070 --> 00:17:57,374
♪ I ONLY WANT TO SEE ♪

346
00:17:57,440 --> 00:17:59,809
ALL RIGHT, THIS HAS BEEN
VERY "TEEN WOLF"-LIKE,

347
00:17:59,876 --> 00:18:03,280
BUT CAN WE PLEASE, UH,
CAN I STOP THE CAR NOW?

348
00:18:09,386 --> 00:18:12,856
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, FUN,
FUN, FUN -- IT'S ALL FUN

349
00:18:12,923 --> 00:18:15,559
WHOO-HOO-HOO!
AND GAMES UNTIL
SOMEONE GETS HURT.

350
00:18:15,625 --> 00:18:17,694
[ LAUGHS ]
WHOO!

351
00:18:17,761 --> 00:18:19,229
[ LAUGHING ]

352
00:18:25,902 --> 00:18:32,175
♪ THAT I KNOW YOU'RE MEANT
TO GIVE YOU SOME ♪♪

353
00:18:32,242 --> 00:18:33,310
ALAN!

354
00:18:33,376 --> 00:18:35,245
A-AH!

355
00:18:35,312 --> 00:18:38,481
[ Panting ] WE'VE BEEN
SCOURING THE WOODS
FOR OVER AN HOUR.

356
00:18:38,548 --> 00:18:39,749
THERE'S NOTHING OUT HERE.

357
00:18:39,816 --> 00:18:41,284
YEAH, WELL, HALF
OF ME BELIEVES

358
00:18:41,351 --> 00:18:43,853
THAT THIS KID IS ON
A REALLY BAD DRUG TRIP,

359
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:45,822
AND I WOULDN'T BE SURPRISED
IF YOU FIND THE OTHER TWO

360
00:18:45,889 --> 00:18:48,658
SCREWING AROUND IN THE BACK
OF THE CAR WITHIN THE HOUR.

361
00:18:48,725 --> 00:18:51,261
You want me to
call it off?
NO.

362
00:18:51,328 --> 00:18:54,331
[ SIGHS ] GREAT.

363
00:18:54,397 --> 00:18:55,365
Ann, hang on.

364
00:18:55,432 --> 00:18:58,602
WHAT?
DENNY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

365
00:19:00,136 --> 00:19:02,973
THE CAR.

366
00:19:03,039 --> 00:19:04,007
I FOUND THE CAR.

367
00:19:05,408 --> 00:19:08,545
WHAT CAN YOU TELL ME
ABOUT THAT '72 CHEVY IMPALA?

368
00:19:10,981 --> 00:19:12,782
A '72 IMPALA?

369
00:19:14,351 --> 00:19:15,652
THAT'S, UH...

370
00:19:17,554 --> 00:19:19,155
THAT'S ALAN'S CAR.
THAT'S RIGHT.

371
00:19:19,222 --> 00:19:21,024
DID YOU F-FIND HER?

372
00:19:21,091 --> 00:19:23,893
IT'S A HEAVILY WOODED
AREA, MR. KLEIN.

373
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:26,963
WHAT ELSE DO YOU REMEMBER?
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

374
00:19:27,030 --> 00:19:28,164
NOTHING, I...

375
00:19:28,231 --> 00:19:29,599
CAN'T REMEMBER...

376
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:32,335
ANYTHING.

377
00:19:32,402 --> 00:19:34,170
YOUR GIRLFRIEND'S LIFE
IS IN DANGER.

378
00:19:34,237 --> 00:19:35,805
DON'T YOU THINK
I KNOW THAT?

379
00:19:37,841 --> 00:19:38,775
[ SIGHS ]

380
00:19:38,842 --> 00:19:41,077
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S KEEP GOING.

381
00:19:44,214 --> 00:19:46,683
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]

382
00:19:49,786 --> 00:19:51,955
ALAN!
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

383
00:19:52,022 --> 00:19:54,124
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

384
00:19:54,190 --> 00:19:56,159
SO, WHAT THE HELL HAVE
YOU BEEN DOING FOR
THE LAST TWO YEARS?

385
00:19:56,226 --> 00:19:59,562
YOU KNOW, MOVIN' AND SHAKIN',
SHAKIN' AND MOVIN'.

386
00:19:59,629 --> 00:20:02,365
[ CLATTERING ]
OH.

387
00:20:10,073 --> 00:20:11,675
IT'S NOT MINE.

388
00:20:13,209 --> 00:20:16,312
YEAH, I'M S-SURE YOU'RE JUST
HOLDING IT FOR A FRIEND.

389
00:20:16,379 --> 00:20:17,747
AS A MATTER OF FACT...

390
00:20:19,249 --> 00:20:21,685
ALAN, AM I INTERRUPTING
SOMETHING?

391
00:20:25,021 --> 00:20:26,956
OKAY, TRUTH?

392
00:20:27,023 --> 00:20:28,958
I'M HOLDING IT FOR NANA.

393
00:20:30,527 --> 00:20:32,662
THAT'S GOOD ENOUGH
FOR ME.

394
00:20:32,729 --> 00:20:33,830
DAVID?

395
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:39,803
[ SIGHS ]

396
00:20:40,770 --> 00:20:42,806
YEAH, YEAH, WHATEVER.

397
00:20:42,872 --> 00:20:45,375
DAVID IS THE WORST
LIAR IN THE WORLD.

398
00:20:45,442 --> 00:20:47,677
YOU KNOW, YOU ASK
HIM A QUESTION,

399
00:20:47,744 --> 00:20:49,412
HE TRIES TO SLIP ONE
PAST YOU.

400
00:20:49,479 --> 00:20:51,448
GET OFF ME.

401
00:20:51,514 --> 00:20:52,782
LISTEN...[SIGHS]

402
00:20:52,849 --> 00:20:54,417
A BUDDY OF MINE BACK HOME
HAS LEFT THE COUNTRY,

403
00:20:54,484 --> 00:20:57,153
AND I'M BABYSITTING.
THAT'S ALL.

404
00:20:57,220 --> 00:20:58,555
END OF STORY.

405
00:21:02,125 --> 00:21:03,526
BE CAREFUL, MAN.

406
00:21:06,596 --> 00:21:08,965
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

407
00:21:15,605 --> 00:21:16,940
HEY, JEN!

408
00:21:18,508 --> 00:21:20,410
[ SIGHS ]

409
00:21:21,745 --> 00:21:23,179
ALL RIGHT, HERE'S
THE QUESTION.

410
00:21:23,246 --> 00:21:26,349
WHAT IS MORE EVOCATIVE --
HIS TANGLE OF WEEDS,

411
00:21:26,416 --> 00:21:28,752
CONSPIRACY OF WEEDS,
OR...

412
00:21:28,818 --> 00:21:30,553
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

413
00:21:30,620 --> 00:21:32,489
CORNUCOPIA OF WEEDS?

414
00:21:34,557 --> 00:21:36,626
DEFINITELY NOT
NUMBER THREE.

415
00:21:38,194 --> 00:21:40,730
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

416
00:21:42,832 --> 00:21:45,702
[ SIGHS ] SO,
I-I WROTE THIS...

417
00:21:45,769 --> 00:21:47,871
[SIGHS] THIS THING.

418
00:21:47,937 --> 00:21:49,405
FOR A CLASS?

419
00:21:49,472 --> 00:21:51,474
NO, NO, NOT FOR A CLASS.

420
00:21:51,541 --> 00:21:53,276
IT'S A...

421
00:21:53,343 --> 00:21:54,744
POEM THING.

422
00:21:57,013 --> 00:21:58,148
SO?

423
00:21:59,349 --> 00:22:01,117
OUT WITH IT.

424
00:22:01,184 --> 00:22:02,318
YEAH?

425
00:22:02,385 --> 00:22:03,686
YEAH.

426
00:22:04,621 --> 00:22:06,756
ALL RIGHT, UH, BE HONEST.

427
00:22:06,823 --> 00:22:08,424
WHEN AM I NOT HONEST?

428
00:22:08,491 --> 00:22:11,561
DON'T HOLD BACK.
JUST BE...BRUTAL.

429
00:22:11,628 --> 00:22:13,296
YOU WANT ME TO HATE IT.

430
00:22:13,363 --> 00:22:15,565
YES.
I CAN DO THAT.

431
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:19,702
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

432
00:22:23,873 --> 00:22:29,078
"HER FEET SOAR,
LEAVE THE EARTH...

433
00:22:29,145 --> 00:22:34,384
"UNINHIBITED BY THE
CONSPIRACY OF WEEDS
THAT ENSNARE ME.

434
00:22:34,450 --> 00:22:37,654
"HER EYES, BLESSED EYES,

435
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:40,824
"PURSUE RAYS OF MOONLIGHT
I AM BLIND TO.

436
00:22:40,890 --> 00:22:45,128
"CAPTURE WONDERS,
REAL WONDERS --

437
00:22:45,195 --> 00:22:48,832
"SHE AND GOD ONLY,
I THINK,

438
00:22:48,898 --> 00:22:51,868
WHICH MY NERVOUS
TENDENCIES DEPRIVE ME."

439
00:22:57,307 --> 00:22:58,575
I MEAN, Y-Y-YOU THINK

440
00:22:58,641 --> 00:23:01,077
THAT "CONSPIRACY" IS --
IS TOO SUBTLE,

441
00:23:01,144 --> 00:23:03,513
OR -- OR HOW ABOUT
"FEET LEAVING THE EARTH" --

442
00:23:03,580 --> 00:23:05,148
I MEAN, TOO COMICAL?

443
00:23:05,215 --> 00:23:08,618
THESE -- THESE DISEMBODIED
FEET JUST -- JUST SOARING,

444
00:23:08,685 --> 00:23:12,055
JUST -- JUST, YOU KNOW,
LIKE, FLYING, LIKE,
OUT THERE OVER--

445
00:23:12,121 --> 00:23:14,657
OVERHEAD, OR...

446
00:23:23,499 --> 00:23:25,501
I HATE IT.

447
00:23:25,568 --> 00:23:26,970
[ CHUCKLES ]

448
00:23:31,174 --> 00:23:32,308
OOH-AHH!

449
00:23:32,375 --> 00:23:33,543
UNH!

450
00:23:33,610 --> 00:23:34,611
WHOO!

451
00:23:34,677 --> 00:23:36,012
NICE SHOT.

452
00:23:36,079 --> 00:23:37,280
7-5.

453
00:23:37,347 --> 00:23:39,616
AH, 7-2.

454
00:23:40,950 --> 00:23:42,619
SO, JENNY --
WHAT'S HER DEAL?

455
00:23:42,685 --> 00:23:45,188
HER DEAL?
IS SHE SOLO?

456
00:23:50,059 --> 00:23:52,595
DATING, GOT A BOYFRIEND?

457
00:23:52,662 --> 00:23:53,830
8-2.

458
00:23:53,897 --> 00:23:55,431
ANYTHING SERIOUS?

459
00:23:55,498 --> 00:23:56,799
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT SERIOUS.

460
00:23:56,866 --> 00:23:59,002
AND I WOULDN'T SAY SHE
HAS A BOYFRIEND.

461
00:23:59,068 --> 00:24:00,737
SHE DOES DATE A LOT.

462
00:24:00,803 --> 00:24:02,772
SHE'S LOOKING.
SO, SHE'S AVAILABLE?

463
00:24:02,839 --> 00:24:03,806
YOU'RE NOT HER TYPE, AL.

464
00:24:03,873 --> 00:24:05,174
WHAT'S HER TYPE?

465
00:24:05,241 --> 00:24:07,710
TRUST ME, SHE'S
TOO SMART FOR YOU.

466
00:24:10,380 --> 00:24:11,581
UNH!

467
00:24:11,648 --> 00:24:13,216
WHEW!

468
00:24:13,283 --> 00:24:14,817
YOU GOT SOMETHING
GOING, DAVID?

469
00:24:14,884 --> 00:24:17,020
[ Panting ] WHAT? NO, NO.

470
00:24:17,086 --> 00:24:19,923
I'M JUST TRYING TO KEEP YOU
FROM HUMILIATING YOURSELF.

471
00:24:19,989 --> 00:24:21,791
'CAUSE IF YOU WANT ME TO
STAY AWAY, I-I'M VERY COOL.

472
00:24:21,858 --> 00:24:25,929
NO, HEY...
YOU'RE A BIG BOY, ALAN.

473
00:24:25,995 --> 00:24:28,097
YOU DO WHAT YOU WANT TO DO.

474
00:24:28,164 --> 00:24:29,432
GOOD.

475
00:24:29,499 --> 00:24:31,167
[ BASKETBALL BOUNCES ]

476
00:24:31,234 --> 00:24:33,770
OOH-AH! [ PANTING ]

477
00:24:33,836 --> 00:24:35,805
[ BIRDS TWEETING ]

478
00:24:41,377 --> 00:24:43,146
HEY.

479
00:24:43,212 --> 00:24:44,547
HEY.

480
00:24:44,614 --> 00:24:47,116
YOU KNOW, THE WHOLE TWINKIE
THING WOULD BE FREAKY ENOUGH

481
00:24:47,183 --> 00:24:49,385
IF YOU DIDN'T ALSO
HAVE TO WEAR IT.

482
00:24:49,452 --> 00:24:50,753
WHERE'S YOUR BOYFRIEND?

483
00:24:50,820 --> 00:24:52,822
OH, HE'S WRITING, I THINK.

484
00:25:01,564 --> 00:25:04,067
[ SMACKING LIPS ]

485
00:25:22,085 --> 00:25:22,885
COME HERE!

486
00:25:22,952 --> 00:25:26,389
HEY, UH...
Man: HELLO?

487
00:25:26,456 --> 00:25:27,790
[ SHRIEKS ]

488
00:25:28,791 --> 00:25:31,060
[ GIGGLING ]

489
00:25:35,498 --> 00:25:37,367
[ KNOCKING ]

490
00:25:40,570 --> 00:25:41,838
[ SIGHS ]

491
00:25:41,904 --> 00:25:44,207
[ LOCK UNLATCHES ]

492
00:25:50,580 --> 00:25:51,914
HEY.

493
00:25:52,749 --> 00:25:54,117
WERE YOU SLEEPIN'?

494
00:25:54,183 --> 00:25:55,184
NO.

495
00:25:55,251 --> 00:25:56,786
NO.

496
00:25:56,853 --> 00:25:58,521
WANT TO SEE
SOMETHING COOL?

497
00:25:58,588 --> 00:26:01,324
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING ]

498
00:26:02,925 --> 00:26:04,861
CUT THE LIGHTS.

499
00:26:14,203 --> 00:26:15,405
[ CHUCKLES ]

500
00:26:19,742 --> 00:26:23,279
[ SIGHS ]

501
00:26:24,681 --> 00:26:27,250
MY OWN PERSONAL GALAXY.

502
00:26:27,316 --> 00:26:28,751
[ SIGHS ]

503
00:26:29,686 --> 00:26:31,120
IT'S COOL.

504
00:26:31,187 --> 00:26:32,388
YEAH.

505
00:26:39,862 --> 00:26:42,298
YOUR FRIEND
ASKED ME OUT.

506
00:26:50,506 --> 00:26:51,974
IT'S JUST A MOVIE.

507
00:26:53,309 --> 00:26:54,777
[ SIGHS ] OH?

508
00:26:56,212 --> 00:26:58,281
AND WHAT MOVIE
ARE YOU GONNA GO SEE?

509
00:26:58,347 --> 00:27:00,483
THAT'S NOT REALLY
THE POINT.

510
00:27:03,586 --> 00:27:05,254
[ SIGHS ]

511
00:27:14,530 --> 00:27:16,065
JEN...

512
00:27:24,207 --> 00:27:26,142
YOU SHOULD TAKE IT SLOW
WITH ALAN.

513
00:27:30,713 --> 00:27:32,482
TAKE IT SLOW WITH ALAN?

514
00:27:32,548 --> 00:27:34,083
YEAH.

515
00:27:34,150 --> 00:27:36,619
YEAH.

516
00:27:36,686 --> 00:27:38,654
HE'S DANGEROUS, JEN.

517
00:27:38,721 --> 00:27:39,722
OH, HE'S DANGEROUS.

518
00:27:39,789 --> 00:27:41,057
YEAH, HE IS.

519
00:27:41,124 --> 00:27:42,525
I'VE SEEN --
I MEAN, FOR A WHILE,

520
00:27:42,592 --> 00:27:46,262
YOU'RE GONNA SEEM LIKE
THE ONLY ONE, YOU KNOW?

521
00:27:48,798 --> 00:27:52,802
JUST -- I'VE SEEN WOMEN
GET FUCKED OVER.

522
00:27:54,604 --> 00:27:56,072
BE CAREFUL.

523
00:27:57,673 --> 00:27:59,041
I WILL.

524
00:28:00,243 --> 00:28:01,511
I PROMISE.

525
00:28:03,713 --> 00:28:05,348
[ BALL BOUNCING ]

526
00:28:05,414 --> 00:28:08,117
[ EMILIANA TORRINI'S "EASY"
PLAYS ]

527
00:28:12,488 --> 00:28:15,858
♪ IT'S NOT AN ACCIDENT ♪
[ LAUGHTER ]

528
00:28:15,925 --> 00:28:18,594
♪ YOU MEANT TO TOUCH ME ♪

529
00:28:18,661 --> 00:28:22,198
♪ AND THAT'S EXACTLY
WHY I'M HERE ♪

530
00:28:22,265 --> 00:28:23,833
I HAD A REALLY GOOD TIME.

531
00:28:23,900 --> 00:28:25,234
YEAH?
YEAH.

532
00:28:25,301 --> 00:28:27,737
♪ A TRICK OF CONFIDENCE ♪
ME TOO.

533
00:28:27,803 --> 00:28:30,473
♪ 20 YEARS INSIDE ♪

534
00:28:30,540 --> 00:28:34,544
♪ YOU'RE EXACTLY WHAT I NEED ♪

535
00:28:34,610 --> 00:28:39,715
♪ DON'T TAKE IT EASY ♪
[ TELEPHONE BEEPING ]

536
00:28:39,782 --> 00:28:43,452
♪ WHY SHOULD WE TAKE IT EASY? ♪
[ Ringing ]

537
00:28:43,519 --> 00:28:45,788
♪ YEAH ♪
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

538
00:28:45,855 --> 00:28:51,060
♪ SHOULD WE TAKE IT EASY? ♪
I SHOULD GET THAT.

539
00:28:51,127 --> 00:28:53,596
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

540
00:29:05,408 --> 00:29:08,778
♪ I BREAK INTO THE PARK ♪

541
00:29:08,844 --> 00:29:11,881
♪ WITH THE INSECTS ♪

542
00:29:11,948 --> 00:29:14,784
♪ STRIKING UP A COSTUME BALL ♪

543
00:29:14,851 --> 00:29:17,320
[ RINGING ]

544
00:29:17,386 --> 00:29:20,790
♪ THE LIGHT IS LOVELY HERE ♪

545
00:29:20,856 --> 00:29:22,692
♪ IN THE NEON GLOW ♪♪

546
00:29:22,758 --> 00:29:25,795
David: DAVID'S MACHINE.
SPEAK NOW.
[ BEEP ]

547
00:29:25,861 --> 00:29:28,831
Jenny: Hey, David, it's Jen.
Pick up the phone.

548
00:29:28,898 --> 00:29:30,833
Pick up the phone,
come on.

549
00:29:30,900 --> 00:29:32,802
It's me.
I know you're there.

550
00:29:32,869 --> 00:29:36,772
I can see your desk lamp is on,
and you always shut it off.

551
00:29:36,839 --> 00:29:38,307
Come on.

552
00:29:38,374 --> 00:29:39,642
All right, fine.
Be that way.

553
00:29:39,709 --> 00:29:41,043
But call me.

554
00:29:45,248 --> 00:29:46,549
WHY ARE WE DOING THIS AGAIN?

555
00:29:46,616 --> 00:29:48,451
I'VE GOT A PORTRAITURE
ASSIGNMENT.

556
00:29:51,787 --> 00:29:52,922
ALL RIGHT.

557
00:29:52,989 --> 00:29:54,924
UM...

558
00:29:54,991 --> 00:29:57,526
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

559
00:29:58,694 --> 00:30:02,832
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

560
00:30:02,898 --> 00:30:05,034
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

561
00:30:09,538 --> 00:30:10,973
WHAT IS IT?

562
00:30:11,040 --> 00:30:12,508
I DON'T KNOW.

563
00:30:14,010 --> 00:30:15,478
SOMETIMES I FEEL LIKE...

564
00:30:18,881 --> 00:30:19,915
LISTEN, I --

565
00:30:19,982 --> 00:30:21,117
I DON'T SAY THIS STUFF MUCH,
OKAY,

566
00:30:21,183 --> 00:30:23,452
SO IT'S GONNA COME OUT
STUPID.

567
00:30:23,519 --> 00:30:26,255
BUT SOMETIMES WHEN I'M AROUND
YOU, I CAN'T BREATHE.

568
00:30:28,057 --> 00:30:30,226
LIKE I'M AFRAID I'LL FUCK UP
THE MOMENT.

569
00:30:31,961 --> 00:30:33,462
IS THAT GOOD OR BAD?

570
00:30:35,464 --> 00:30:37,400
GOOD.

571
00:30:37,466 --> 00:30:39,402
[ CHUCKLES ]

572
00:30:42,305 --> 00:30:43,773
I WAS THINKING
ABOUT WHAT YOU SAID

573
00:30:43,839 --> 00:30:48,377
ABOUT, UM, THE BEAUTY
OF THE IMPULSIVE ACT.

574
00:30:48,444 --> 00:30:51,180
IT'S WHAT I STRIVE FOR.
IT'S LIKE ALL --

575
00:30:51,247 --> 00:30:52,581
ALL GREAT PHOTOGRAPHERS --

576
00:30:52,648 --> 00:30:55,451
I MEAN, THEY HAD, IT'S JUST
THIS THING THAT JUST --

577
00:30:55,518 --> 00:30:58,220
IT'S JUST THIS IDEA,
JUST THIS ITCH

578
00:30:58,287 --> 00:31:01,357
THAT JUST STARTS AT THE BASE
OF YOUR SPINE AND --

579
00:31:01,424 --> 00:31:03,793
GOD, I HATE IT
WHEN I CAN'T TALK.

580
00:31:03,859 --> 00:31:04,927
[ ZIPPER UNZIPS ]

581
00:31:04,994 --> 00:31:06,362
I HATE IT

582
00:31:06,429 --> 00:31:08,731
WHEN I KNOW EXACTLY WHAT IT IS
THAT I WANT TO SAY,

583
00:31:08,798 --> 00:31:10,299
AND I CAN'T.

584
00:31:10,366 --> 00:31:12,268
DO YOU EVER GET THAT?

585
00:31:12,335 --> 00:31:14,003
MM...

586
00:31:17,239 --> 00:31:19,208
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

587
00:31:22,778 --> 00:31:24,313
WOW.

588
00:31:27,750 --> 00:31:30,686
[ WOMAN VOCALIZING ]

589
00:31:30,753 --> 00:31:32,088
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

590
00:31:32,154 --> 00:31:35,424
NO HANDS. [ LAUGHS ]
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

591
00:31:35,491 --> 00:31:37,126
[ LAUGHING ]

592
00:31:38,761 --> 00:31:40,096
OKAY.

593
00:31:41,063 --> 00:31:43,132
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

594
00:31:57,279 --> 00:31:59,248
[ VOCALIZING CONTINUES ]

595
00:32:01,917 --> 00:32:03,886
[ LAUGHS ]

596
00:32:03,953 --> 00:32:05,821
[ GASPS ]

597
00:32:24,974 --> 00:32:27,309
[ CAMERA CLANKS ]

598
00:32:27,376 --> 00:32:30,112
[ VOCALIZING CONTINUES ]

599
00:32:34,917 --> 00:32:37,586
[ RINGING ]

600
00:32:37,653 --> 00:32:39,789
David: DAVID'S MACHINE.
SPEAK NOW.

601
00:32:39,855 --> 00:32:41,157
[ BEEP ]

602
00:32:41,223 --> 00:32:43,759
Jenny: David, it's Jenny...
again.

603
00:32:43,826 --> 00:32:46,929
I'm at home.
You should call me.

604
00:32:46,996 --> 00:32:48,764
Your desk light is on.

605
00:32:48,831 --> 00:32:50,866
You are very busted.

606
00:32:50,933 --> 00:32:53,169
Now, I'm not sure
why you're not ca--

607
00:32:53,235 --> 00:32:55,104
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

608
00:32:55,171 --> 00:32:57,706
[ VOCALIZING CONTINUES ]

609
00:33:25,234 --> 00:33:27,703
[ VOCALIZING CONTINUES ]

610
00:33:33,542 --> 00:33:36,278
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

611
00:33:41,617 --> 00:33:43,752
SINCE WHEN DO I HAVE TO
TRACK YOU DOWN?

612
00:33:47,189 --> 00:33:48,824
EXCUSE ME.

613
00:33:52,061 --> 00:33:54,396
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED
TO DO HERE?

614
00:33:54,463 --> 00:33:56,198
LOOK, I'M TRYING TO RESPECT
YOUR FEELINGS

615
00:33:56,265 --> 00:33:58,567
AND STILL, YOU KNOW,
LISTEN TO MINE.

616
00:33:58,634 --> 00:34:00,102
CAN WE AT LEAST TALK
ABOUT THIS, PLEASE?

617
00:34:00,169 --> 00:34:01,537
SURE, WE CAN TALK,

618
00:34:01,604 --> 00:34:03,439
AS LONG AS YOU PROMISE
TO TAKE THINGS SLOWLY.

619
00:34:03,506 --> 00:34:04,673
DAVID...
NO.

620
00:34:04,740 --> 00:34:06,475
I GAVE YOU A PIECE
OF ADVICE, JEN,

621
00:34:06,542 --> 00:34:08,611
AND YOU TOTALLY
DISREGARDED IT.

622
00:34:08,677 --> 00:34:11,714
SO GREAT.
HAVE FUN.

623
00:34:11,780 --> 00:34:14,650
YOU REALLY EXPECT ME TO BELIEVE
THAT YOU'RE THIS UPSET

624
00:34:14,717 --> 00:34:17,219
BECAUSE I DIDN'T TAKE
YOUR ADVICE?

625
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:20,589
BELIEVE WHATEVER
YOU WANT, JEN.

626
00:34:20,656 --> 00:34:22,892
WHAT WOULD YOU KNOW ABOUT
ANY OF THIS, DAVID?

627
00:34:22,958 --> 00:34:25,327
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME YOU EVEN
APPROACHED ROMANTIC NOTION

628
00:34:25,394 --> 00:34:27,229
THAT WASN'T ON PAPER?

629
00:34:33,269 --> 00:34:34,603
SO HE'S IT?

630
00:34:35,905 --> 00:34:37,206
HE'S THE ONE?

631
00:34:39,975 --> 00:34:41,911
[ WOMAN VOCALIZING ]

632
00:34:43,479 --> 00:34:45,314
I'M REALLY HAPPY FOR YOU.

633
00:34:56,191 --> 00:34:58,494
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

634
00:35:13,542 --> 00:35:15,344
SPAZ!

635
00:35:16,245 --> 00:35:17,546
HEY!

636
00:35:18,714 --> 00:35:20,716
I TALKED TO A GUY
FROM ACROSS THE HALL.

637
00:35:20,783 --> 00:35:22,518
HE SAID YOU LEFT
WITH A KITE.

638
00:35:24,687 --> 00:35:25,988
I COULDN'T FIND THE ONE
I USED TO BRING,

639
00:35:26,055 --> 00:35:29,558
SO I BOUGHT A NEW ONE
AND DECORATED IT MYSELF.

640
00:35:32,895 --> 00:35:34,063
YES, IT IS MY ASS,

641
00:35:34,129 --> 00:35:36,332
AND I FIGURE THIS IS HOW YOU
SEE ME FOR THE TIME BEING,

642
00:35:36,398 --> 00:35:39,435
SO I MIGHT AS WELL BE PROUD
OF IT, ACCEPT IT,

643
00:35:39,501 --> 00:35:41,737
AND SHOW IT OFF
FOR THE WORLD TO SEE.

644
00:35:41,804 --> 00:35:43,839
I MEAN, THE PEOPLE AT KINKO'S
WERE NONE TOO HAPPY,

645
00:35:43,906 --> 00:35:45,507
BUT, HEY, FUCK 'EM.

646
00:35:45,574 --> 00:35:47,710
NOTHING A LITTLE WINDEX
WON'T TAKE CARE OF, RIGHT?

647
00:35:50,012 --> 00:35:51,680
[ GRUNTS ]

648
00:35:51,747 --> 00:35:53,716
WHOA!

649
00:35:53,782 --> 00:35:54,883
FUCK!

650
00:35:57,019 --> 00:35:58,020
ALL RIGHT.

651
00:35:58,087 --> 00:35:59,421
ALL RIGHT.

652
00:36:05,060 --> 00:36:08,797
HEY, DO YOU WANT TO
KEEP YOUR ASS UNDER
CONTROL THERE, PAL?

653
00:36:17,640 --> 00:36:18,907
A LITTLE KITE LESSON.

654
00:36:20,275 --> 00:36:21,710
TO THE CASUAL OBSERVER,

655
00:36:21,777 --> 00:36:25,748
IT WOULD APPEAR THAT THE STRING

656
00:36:25,814 --> 00:36:28,250
IS HOLDING THE KITE BACK --

657
00:36:28,317 --> 00:36:31,787
WITHOUT THE STRING, THE KITE
WOULD ESCAPE THE EARTH.

658
00:36:33,622 --> 00:36:38,093
THE REALITY --
THE STRING IS THE ANCHOR.

659
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:40,896
IT'S THE STRUCTURE
THAT ALLOWS THE KITE TO SOAR.

660
00:36:45,267 --> 00:36:46,735
WITHOUT IT...

661
00:36:52,041 --> 00:36:53,575
...UTTER CHAOS.

662
00:36:56,545 --> 00:36:58,013
SO YOU'RE THE STRING?

663
00:36:59,014 --> 00:37:00,115
SHE'S THE KITE?

664
00:37:01,850 --> 00:37:03,052
WHAT AM I?

665
00:37:08,624 --> 00:37:09,758
TALK TO HER, MAN.

666
00:37:09,825 --> 00:37:11,560
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING TO SAY,
ALAN.

667
00:37:12,561 --> 00:37:14,496
YOU'RE REALLY
FUCKING HER UP.

668
00:37:14,563 --> 00:37:17,032
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

669
00:37:17,099 --> 00:37:18,267
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

670
00:37:18,333 --> 00:37:20,269
I MEAN, I KNOW YOU, ALAN.

671
00:37:20,335 --> 00:37:22,471
I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE CAPABLE OF.

672
00:37:24,373 --> 00:37:25,708
SHE DOESN'T.

673
00:37:26,675 --> 00:37:28,110
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT SUSAN.

674
00:37:28,177 --> 00:37:29,445
SUSAN, RENEE, JACKIE.

675
00:37:29,511 --> 00:37:30,546
I'VE CHANGED THAT SHIT!

676
00:37:30,612 --> 00:37:32,114
PEOPLE DON'T CHANGE, ALAN.

677
00:37:32,181 --> 00:37:34,983
COME ON, DAVID. IT WAS THREE
FUCKING YEARS AGO, MAN.

678
00:37:36,485 --> 00:37:39,688
YOU KNOW, I THOUGHT I COULD
DO THIS, ALAN, BUT I CAN'T.

679
00:37:43,125 --> 00:37:45,461
WHAT IF I ASKED YOU
TO WALK AWAY FROM JENNY?

680
00:37:46,962 --> 00:37:48,964
WHAT IF I TOLD YOU
I COULDN'T DO THAT?

681
00:37:55,037 --> 00:37:56,438
FUCK.

682
00:37:57,606 --> 00:38:00,008
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING ]

683
00:38:04,947 --> 00:38:07,483
[ DOOR OPENS ]

684
00:38:11,387 --> 00:38:13,789
HUH? OH.

685
00:38:13,856 --> 00:38:15,491
WHA--

686
00:38:15,557 --> 00:38:18,060
W-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

687
00:38:18,127 --> 00:38:19,495
SHH.
O-O W!

688
00:38:19,561 --> 00:38:20,963
GO BACK TO SLEEP.

689
00:38:21,029 --> 00:38:25,167
YOU BETTER HOPE YOU GOT IT
TIED TIGHT BACK THERE.

690
00:38:25,234 --> 00:38:27,169
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

691
00:38:28,370 --> 00:38:30,139
[ Muffled ] MOTHERFUCKER!

692
00:38:30,205 --> 00:38:31,206
ALAN...

693
00:38:31,273 --> 00:38:32,274
GET IN.

694
00:38:32,341 --> 00:38:33,342
UNTIE ME!

695
00:38:33,409 --> 00:38:34,376
WHAT?

696
00:38:34,443 --> 00:38:35,611
UNTIE ME RIGHT NOW!

697
00:38:35,677 --> 00:38:37,112
DON'T MAKE ME USE THESE.

698
00:38:39,848 --> 00:38:42,017
CAN'T YOU HELP ME
OUT HERE?!

699
00:38:43,719 --> 00:38:44,987
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

700
00:38:46,955 --> 00:38:48,924
Jenny:
WHERE ARE WE GOING, ALAN?

701
00:38:48,991 --> 00:38:50,626
JUST RELAX.

702
00:38:50,692 --> 00:38:53,328
ENJOY THE RIDE.

703
00:38:53,395 --> 00:38:55,931
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

704
00:39:04,339 --> 00:39:06,375
[ ENGINE STOPS ]

705
00:39:06,441 --> 00:39:08,110
WE'RE HERE.

706
00:39:08,177 --> 00:39:09,211
[ SIGHS ]

707
00:39:09,278 --> 00:39:10,579
WHERE?

708
00:39:13,248 --> 00:39:14,917
[ SIGHS ]

709
00:39:22,658 --> 00:39:24,126
FUCK IT.

710
00:39:41,643 --> 00:39:43,245
THIS IS SO STUPID.

711
00:39:56,458 --> 00:40:00,662
ALLERTON, BUILT IN 1923
BY A MAN NAMED VERNON BROWN --

712
00:40:00,729 --> 00:40:02,598
MILLIONAIRE.

713
00:40:02,664 --> 00:40:05,067
HE HAD TWO SONS
AND A WIFE WHO DIED.

714
00:40:05,133 --> 00:40:07,536
THE YOUNGEST SON
WAS A FUCKING GENIUS --

715
00:40:07,603 --> 00:40:09,738
A REGULAR EINSTEIN --

716
00:40:09,805 --> 00:40:13,008
SHIT LIKE WRITING A SYMPHONY
BY THE TIME HE WAS 15.

717
00:40:13,075 --> 00:40:16,011
THE OTHER SON -- ONE DISASTER
AFTER ANOTHER.

718
00:40:16,078 --> 00:40:20,115
OKAY, SO, EVENTUALLY,
BAD SON KILLS TWO WOMEN.

719
00:40:20,182 --> 00:40:21,850
SO WHEN THE COPS COME
TO PUT HIM AWAY,

720
00:40:21,917 --> 00:40:25,354
BAD BOY ESCAPES
AND DISAPPEARS.

721
00:40:25,420 --> 00:40:27,990
SO VERNON HITS THE ROAD
IN SEARCH OF BAD BOY.

722
00:40:28,056 --> 00:40:30,259
FIGURES HE'LL FIND HIM
AND CLEAR HIS NAME.

723
00:40:30,325 --> 00:40:32,694
HE SPENDS TWO YEARS
LOOKING EVERYWHERE.

724
00:40:32,761 --> 00:40:35,464
AND WHEN HE FINALLY GETS BACK
TO THE HOUSE, IT'S EMPTY.

725
00:40:35,530 --> 00:40:37,032
THE GOOD SON'S GONE.

726
00:40:37,099 --> 00:40:39,902
THE OLD MAN SPENT THE REST
OF HIS LIFE ALONE.

727
00:40:39,968 --> 00:40:42,704
SPENT EVERY DOLLAR HE EVER HAD
BUILDING THIS PLACE.

728
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:47,976
THIS IS A PLACE WHERE A GUY
SPENT EVERY BUCK HE EVER HAD

729
00:40:48,043 --> 00:40:50,646
TRYING TO MAKE PEACE
AFTER IT WAS TOO LATE.

730
00:40:55,083 --> 00:40:56,251
SIT.

731
00:40:57,552 --> 00:40:58,954
EXCUSE ME?

732
00:41:02,424 --> 00:41:04,826
BOTH OF YOU, SIT.

733
00:41:06,695 --> 00:41:08,730
[ SIGHS ]

734
00:41:17,606 --> 00:41:19,274
WE MATTER --

735
00:41:19,341 --> 00:41:20,742
THE THREE OF US.

736
00:41:20,809 --> 00:41:22,210
NOW, I KNOW WE HAVE
SOME ISSUES HERE,

737
00:41:22,277 --> 00:41:26,682
BUT FROM THIS MOMENT ON,
I WANT EVERYONE TO DEAL.

738
00:41:26,748 --> 00:41:28,617
SO LET'S ALL SAY
WE'RE SORRY,

739
00:41:28,684 --> 00:41:29,718
HUG A LITTLE,

740
00:41:29,785 --> 00:41:31,386
AND GET THIS SHOW
ON THE ROAD.

741
00:41:33,021 --> 00:41:34,856
COME ON, I WANT A HUG!

742
00:41:35,857 --> 00:41:37,092
THIS IS SO RIDICULOUS.

743
00:41:37,159 --> 00:41:39,795
I SAID...HUG!

744
00:41:59,514 --> 00:42:00,649
I...

745
00:42:00,716 --> 00:42:01,950
WANT...

746
00:42:02,017 --> 00:42:03,452
A HUG.

747
00:42:03,518 --> 00:42:05,420
ALAN, STOP IT.

748
00:42:06,722 --> 00:42:08,190
WOULD YOU STOP?!

749
00:42:10,559 --> 00:42:12,861
YOU CAN'T DO THAT!

750
00:42:12,928 --> 00:42:14,029
YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED
TO DO THAT!

751
00:42:14,096 --> 00:42:15,464
YOU CAN'T FORCE US
TO MATTER, ALAN!

752
00:42:15,530 --> 00:42:18,433
YOU CAN'T JUST --
YOU CAN'T JUST SAY, "OKAY,"

753
00:42:18,500 --> 00:42:20,235
AND THEN, LIKE MAGIC,
EVERYTHING GOES BACK TO NORMAL!

754
00:42:20,302 --> 00:42:22,371
THIS IS AMERICA, ALAN!
REALLY!

755
00:42:22,437 --> 00:42:24,639
[ As David ] "THIS IS AMERICA,
ALAN! REALLY!"

756
00:42:24,706 --> 00:42:26,174
[ CHUCKLES ]

757
00:42:28,143 --> 00:42:29,011
[ CHUCKLES ]

758
00:42:29,077 --> 00:42:30,812
WHAT THE FUCK IS THAT,
DAVID?

759
00:42:32,447 --> 00:42:33,648
NO.

760
00:42:33,715 --> 00:42:35,384
NO.

761
00:42:37,219 --> 00:42:38,353
LOOK, GUYS...

762
00:42:39,721 --> 00:42:41,690
I KNOW HOW THESE THINGS GO.

763
00:42:41,757 --> 00:42:43,458
AND I DON'T THINK THAT --

764
00:42:43,525 --> 00:42:49,598
NO, ACTUALLY, I KNOW THAT I
DON'T WANT TO BE A THIRD WHEEL.

765
00:42:49,664 --> 00:42:52,334
WE'RE NOT A BICYCLE, DAVID.

766
00:42:52,401 --> 00:42:53,869
WE'RE FRIENDS.

767
00:42:55,704 --> 00:42:57,105
YOU DO MATTER.

768
00:42:59,441 --> 00:43:01,076
YOU WILL ALWAYS MATTER.

769
00:43:02,344 --> 00:43:03,812
DON'T YOU KNOW THAT?

770
00:43:03,879 --> 00:43:05,047
[ CHUCKLES ]

771
00:43:08,216 --> 00:43:10,952
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

772
00:43:20,429 --> 00:43:22,197
HAPPY?

773
00:43:22,264 --> 00:43:25,100
IN A GREAT DEAL OF PAIN,
ACTUALLY.

774
00:43:27,202 --> 00:43:28,303
GOOD.

775
00:43:28,370 --> 00:43:29,371
[ LAUGHS ]

776
00:43:33,708 --> 00:43:35,410
Jenny: ALAN?

777
00:43:35,477 --> 00:43:36,478
David: ALAN?

778
00:43:36,545 --> 00:43:37,846
ALAN?

779
00:43:41,917 --> 00:43:43,485
DID YOU FIND HIM YET?

780
00:43:43,552 --> 00:43:45,554
AAAAAAAAAAHH!

781
00:43:45,620 --> 00:43:47,089
HA HA HA!

782
00:43:49,224 --> 00:43:50,726
HI.

783
00:43:50,792 --> 00:43:52,260
MEET MY NEW FRIEND.

784
00:43:54,196 --> 00:43:56,131
[ CHUCKLING ]

785
00:43:57,199 --> 00:43:58,200
YOU!

786
00:43:58,266 --> 00:44:00,735
WHOA! NO!

787
00:44:00,802 --> 00:44:02,337
NO! NO, NO!

788
00:44:02,404 --> 00:44:03,371
AHH-AHH!

789
00:44:03,438 --> 00:44:05,273
MY -- MY FRIEND!
MY -- MY FRIEND!

790
00:44:05,340 --> 00:44:07,476
[ Echoing ] WHERE THE FUCK
IS MY FRIEND?

791
00:44:12,247 --> 00:44:15,884
WE SHOULD STOP NOW, WHILE
EVERYTHING IS PERFECT.

792
00:44:15,951 --> 00:44:18,253
WE SHOULD JUST GRAB HOLD
OF EACH OTHER...

793
00:44:19,654 --> 00:44:21,123
AND FREEZE TIME.

794
00:44:24,893 --> 00:44:28,430
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS]

795
00:44:40,876 --> 00:44:43,478
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

796
00:44:43,545 --> 00:44:45,447
SO, WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

797
00:44:45,514 --> 00:44:46,548
WHO, VERNON?

798
00:44:46,615 --> 00:44:48,450
HE GOT CLUBBED TO DEATH
WITH A SHOVEL.

799
00:44:48,517 --> 00:44:49,618
WOW.
SHIT.

800
00:44:49,684 --> 00:44:51,052
NO, BUT HERE'S THE KICKER.

801
00:44:51,119 --> 00:44:53,388
WHEN THEY FOUND HIM DEAD,
HE HAD A LOADED SHOTGUN.

802
00:44:53,455 --> 00:44:56,424
SO HE KNEW HIS KILLER,
JUST LET HIM DO IT.

803
00:44:56,491 --> 00:44:58,360
SO BAD SON CAME BACK?

804
00:44:58,426 --> 00:45:00,729
THAT'S THE THEORY.

805
00:45:00,795 --> 00:45:02,264
HM.

806
00:45:04,833 --> 00:45:06,902
OKAY, GUYS.
LET'S SEE IT.

807
00:45:08,503 --> 00:45:10,172
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

808
00:45:10,238 --> 00:45:11,439
BEAUTIFUL.

809
00:45:12,574 --> 00:45:14,709
COME ON!

810
00:45:14,776 --> 00:45:17,312
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

811
00:45:17,379 --> 00:45:18,346
MORE, MORE.

812
00:45:18,413 --> 00:45:19,681
DAVID, MORE.

813
00:45:19,748 --> 00:45:21,583
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

814
00:45:21,650 --> 00:45:23,518
DAVID, CATCH.

815
00:45:31,059 --> 00:45:33,528
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

816
00:45:33,595 --> 00:45:35,063
ALL RIGHT.

817
00:45:35,130 --> 00:45:37,265
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]
YOU GOT IT.

818
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:40,602
15 MINUTES, MAN.

819
00:45:40,669 --> 00:45:42,470
WHAT?

820
00:45:42,537 --> 00:45:43,939
WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

821
00:45:44,005 --> 00:45:46,241
WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

822
00:45:46,308 --> 00:45:48,577
WHOO!

823
00:45:48,643 --> 00:45:50,378
[ LAUGHS ]

824
00:45:51,413 --> 00:45:52,547
WHOO!

825
00:45:52,614 --> 00:45:54,783
[ LAUGHTER ]

826
00:45:54,849 --> 00:45:58,186
WHOO-HOO!
WHOO!

827
00:45:58,253 --> 00:45:59,888
[ SIGHS ]

828
00:46:04,092 --> 00:46:06,628
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

829
00:46:11,600 --> 00:46:13,535
[ MOANING ]

830
00:46:17,572 --> 00:46:18,974
I LOVE YOU.

831
00:46:31,786 --> 00:46:33,922
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

832
00:46:44,900 --> 00:46:47,302
[ JENNY SCREAMING ]

833
00:46:47,369 --> 00:46:49,371
SOMEONE WENT POSTAL
ON THIS THING.

834
00:46:49,437 --> 00:46:51,273
CHECK THE TRUNK
FOR INITIALS.

835
00:46:52,907 --> 00:46:54,576
[ SIGHS ]

836
00:46:54,643 --> 00:46:56,711
THIS IS THE ONE.

837
00:46:56,778 --> 00:46:58,446
Any sign of anyone?

838
00:46:58,513 --> 00:46:59,881
SORRY.

839
00:46:59,948 --> 00:47:03,218
All right, get up to the house
as fast as you can.

840
00:47:04,452 --> 00:47:05,920
OH, BOY.

841
00:47:05,987 --> 00:47:08,323
[ GUNSHOT ]

842
00:47:08,390 --> 00:47:10,091
♪ POP, YOU GOT TO MAKE
THINGS RIGHT ♪

843
00:47:10,158 --> 00:47:11,660
♪ IT'S ON TOP ♪

844
00:47:11,726 --> 00:47:15,597
♪ MAKE THINGS RIGHT ♪
[ ALAN CHUCKLING ]

845
00:47:15,664 --> 00:47:17,899
[ HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING ]

846
00:47:17,966 --> 00:47:20,735
YOU SHOULD FINISH
YOUR JOKE.

847
00:47:20,802 --> 00:47:23,004
YOU SHOULD
GO TALK TO HER. WHAT?

848
00:47:23,071 --> 00:47:24,906
YEAH, DAVID.
ASK HER OUT.

849
00:47:24,973 --> 00:47:26,041
NO.

850
00:47:26,107 --> 00:47:27,175
WE KNOW YOU WERE CONSIDERING

851
00:47:27,242 --> 00:47:28,877
THE POLITICAL RAMIFICATIONS

852
00:47:28,943 --> 00:47:30,612
OF "PROWST'S" ROMANTICISM.

853
00:47:30,679 --> 00:47:34,316
IT'S PROUST,
AND HE WASN'T POLITICAL.

854
00:47:34,382 --> 00:47:36,384
HE WAS HARDLY A ROMANTIC.

855
00:47:36,451 --> 00:47:38,687
WHAT ABOUT HIS LEGS?
NOT AS GOOD AS HERS.

856
00:47:38,753 --> 00:47:41,189
Jenny: DAVID...

857
00:47:41,256 --> 00:47:42,624
FORGET IT, OKAY?

858
00:47:42,691 --> 00:47:44,326
IT'S JUST RIDICULOUS.

859
00:47:44,392 --> 00:47:47,162
FUCK IT.
NO! ALAN!

860
00:47:49,230 --> 00:47:51,032
HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

861
00:47:51,099 --> 00:47:52,867
[ LAUGHS ]
[ LAUGHS ]

862
00:47:52,934 --> 00:47:55,003
HE IS TRULY AMAZING.

863
00:47:55,070 --> 00:48:00,075
YOU KNOW THERE WERE THESE TWO
GIRLS, FRESHMAN YEAR --

864
00:48:00,141 --> 00:48:01,543
RENEE AND JACKIE.

865
00:48:01,609 --> 00:48:06,481
ALAN MET THEM BOTH AT A BAR,
AND THEY BOTH TOOK THE BAIT,

866
00:48:06,548 --> 00:48:10,685
AND HE'S GOING BACK AND FORTH
BETWEEN THEM, FRESHMAN YEAR...

867
00:48:10,752 --> 00:48:13,855
UNTIL THEY FOUND OUT
ABOUT EACH OTHER.

868
00:48:13,922 --> 00:48:15,390
AND THEN HE GOT DUMPED?

869
00:48:15,457 --> 00:48:17,826
NO. THEN HE HAD A THREESOME.

870
00:48:17,892 --> 00:48:19,194
IT WAS --

871
00:48:19,260 --> 00:48:20,228
I COME --

872
00:48:20,295 --> 00:48:22,263
I COME BACK TO THE DORM

873
00:48:22,330 --> 00:48:29,471
AND FIND THIS MASS OF FLESH
AND CONDOM WRAPPERS EVERY--
DAVID...

874
00:48:29,537 --> 00:48:32,707
WHY WOULD YOU
TELL ME THAT?

875
00:48:32,774 --> 00:48:34,175
SORRY.

876
00:48:35,877 --> 00:48:37,545
[ SIGHS ]

877
00:48:37,612 --> 00:48:38,713
PIECE OF CAKE.

878
00:48:41,149 --> 00:48:42,484
WHAT?

879
00:48:43,518 --> 00:48:44,652
NOTHING.

880
00:48:47,122 --> 00:48:48,623
SO, WHAT'D YOU TELL HER?

881
00:48:48,690 --> 00:48:50,291
OH, THAT DAVID WAS THE FIRST
LIVING RECIPIENT

882
00:48:50,358 --> 00:48:51,626
OF A BABOON'S PENIS,

883
00:48:51,693 --> 00:48:53,661
AND THAT HE WANTED
TO TRY IT OUT.

884
00:48:53,728 --> 00:48:55,597
[ LAUGHS ]

885
00:48:55,663 --> 00:48:57,499
WHAT?

886
00:48:57,565 --> 00:48:59,567
YOU WHAT?

887
00:48:59,634 --> 00:49:01,736
HER NAME IS ELISE.

888
00:49:01,803 --> 00:49:03,138
YOU SHOULD CALL HER.

889
00:49:08,777 --> 00:49:09,744
[ LAUGHS ]

890
00:49:09,811 --> 00:49:10,812
YOU'RE CRAZY!

891
00:49:10,879 --> 00:49:11,946
[ Ringing ]

892
00:49:12,013 --> 00:49:13,014
Elise: Hello?

893
00:49:13,081 --> 00:49:14,249
HELLO, UH, ELISE?

894
00:49:14,315 --> 00:49:16,885
Hello?
Who is this, please?

895
00:49:16,951 --> 00:49:18,253
YEAH, HI, THIS IS D--

896
00:49:18,319 --> 00:49:19,721
[ Chuckles ] Gotcha.

897
00:49:19,788 --> 00:49:22,190
Leave a thingy
at the whatchamacallit.

898
00:49:22,257 --> 00:49:24,759
[ Beep ]

899
00:49:24,826 --> 00:49:27,729
UH...HI.

900
00:49:27,796 --> 00:49:30,698
HI. UH, GOD, THIS IS --

901
00:49:30,765 --> 00:49:31,800
OH, THIS IS AWKWARD.

902
00:49:31,866 --> 00:49:34,302
UM...WE WERE SORT OF
INTRODUCED...

903
00:49:34,369 --> 00:49:37,105
[ MOCEAN WORKER'S
"TRES TRES CHIC" PLAYS ]

904
00:49:40,809 --> 00:49:42,210
ELISE.

905
00:49:43,812 --> 00:49:45,013
DAVID?

906
00:49:45,079 --> 00:49:46,714
YEAH.

907
00:49:46,781 --> 00:49:48,216
OH, I'M SORRY.

908
00:49:48,283 --> 00:49:51,586
I WAS WAITING OUT FRONT FOR,
LIKE, 10 MINUTES, AND --

909
00:49:51,653 --> 00:49:53,254
[ LAUGHS ]

910
00:49:53,321 --> 00:49:55,623
WELL, YOU KNOW...

911
00:49:55,690 --> 00:49:57,692
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA BE
THE OTHER GUY.

912
00:50:00,962 --> 00:50:02,697
NO.

913
00:50:02,764 --> 00:50:04,732
NO.

914
00:50:04,799 --> 00:50:06,201
I-I'M JUST ME.

915
00:50:37,799 --> 00:50:39,734
[ SIGHS ]

916
00:50:39,801 --> 00:50:41,436
ELISE STEVENS.

917
00:50:44,939 --> 00:50:46,174
DAVID KLEIN.

918
00:50:46,241 --> 00:50:48,510
WHY DON'T WE
JUST START OVER?

919
00:50:48,576 --> 00:50:50,178
SO, YOU'RE A WRITER,
HUH?

920
00:50:50,245 --> 00:50:51,713
[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH.

921
00:50:51,779 --> 00:50:53,681
I ONCE MET A WRITER.

922
00:50:53,748 --> 00:50:55,183
WELL, KIND OF.

923
00:50:55,250 --> 00:50:56,818
HE CAME TO MY HIGH SCHOOL.

924
00:50:56,885 --> 00:50:58,987
HE WAS THAT GUY
WHO WROTE THAT PLAY

925
00:50:59,053 --> 00:51:02,657
ABOUT THAT GUY WHOSE FATHER
WAS KILLED BY HIS UNCLE,

926
00:51:02,724 --> 00:51:04,192
AND HE WAS FUCKING
HIS MOTHER,

927
00:51:04,259 --> 00:51:06,694
AND THEN, AT THE END,
EVERYBODY DIES.

928
00:51:06,761 --> 00:51:09,964
YOU KNOW.
THEY MADE IT INTO A MOVIE.

929
00:51:10,031 --> 00:51:11,032
"HAMLET"?

930
00:51:11,099 --> 00:51:13,001
YEAH.

931
00:51:13,067 --> 00:51:14,736
I DIDN'T SEE IT.

932
00:51:14,802 --> 00:51:16,838
IT LOOKED DUMB.

933
00:51:16,905 --> 00:51:18,606
WHOA, WHOA.
W-WAIT. WAIT A SECOND.

934
00:51:18,673 --> 00:51:22,110
UH...Y-Y-YOU MET
THE WRITER?

935
00:51:22,177 --> 00:51:25,413
Y-YOU MET
W-WILLIAM SHAKESPEARE?

936
00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:27,682
UH-HUH. GOT TO
SWORD-FIGHT WITH HIM.

937
00:51:28,883 --> 00:51:29,851
UH...

938
00:51:29,918 --> 00:51:31,386
HE'S DEAD.

939
00:51:31,452 --> 00:51:33,121
SHAKESPEARE?

940
00:51:33,187 --> 00:51:35,256
I MEAN,REALLY DEAD.

941
00:51:35,323 --> 00:51:37,859
[ Laughing ] I'M KIDDING.

942
00:51:37,926 --> 00:51:38,960
[ LAUGHS ]

943
00:51:39,027 --> 00:51:42,063
HE WAS AN ACTOR
DRESSED LIKE SHAKESPEARE.

944
00:51:42,130 --> 00:51:43,531
HE HAD ALL THESE SCENES.

945
00:51:43,598 --> 00:51:47,035
HE WAS LIKE
THIS SIDESHOW FREAK --

946
00:51:47,101 --> 00:51:50,338
TOTALLY FUCKING BORING.

947
00:51:50,405 --> 00:51:53,341
HE NEEDED A VOLUNTEER.
MY FRIENDS MADE ME DO IT.

948
00:51:53,408 --> 00:51:54,742
[ CHUCKLES ]

949
00:51:54,809 --> 00:51:57,512
11 SECONDS OF GLORY
UNTIL HE DISARMED ME

950
00:51:57,579 --> 00:52:00,448
AND GOT ME
INTO A HALF NELSON.

951
00:52:00,515 --> 00:52:02,951
I THINK HE WAS
TRYING TO FEEL ME UP.

952
00:52:03,017 --> 00:52:06,354
[ CHUCKLES ]
LIKE YOUR FRIEND
THE OTHER NIGHT.

953
00:52:06,421 --> 00:52:08,456
WHAT'S THE DEAL
WITH THAT GUY ANYWAY?

954
00:52:08,523 --> 00:52:10,158
OH, ALAN. RIGHT.

955
00:52:10,224 --> 00:52:11,926
UM...

956
00:52:11,993 --> 00:52:13,394
HE'S GOT A GIRLFRIEND.

957
00:52:14,696 --> 00:52:15,897
OH.

958
00:52:18,499 --> 00:52:19,834
YOU WANT TO COME UP?

959
00:52:19,901 --> 00:52:21,769
[ CREAKS ]

960
00:52:21,836 --> 00:52:25,139
SO, WHAT IS IT,
"HO" TO "HOR"?
NO. Y-YOU HAVE "H-O-R-S."

961
00:52:25,206 --> 00:52:26,608
I HAVE NOTHING.

962
00:52:27,809 --> 00:52:28,810
ALL RIGHT.

963
00:52:28,876 --> 00:52:31,446
[ CHUCKLES ]

964
00:52:31,512 --> 00:52:33,481
EYES CLOSED,
STANDING ON ONE LEG.

965
00:52:36,784 --> 00:52:38,453
[ LAUGHS ]

966
00:52:38,519 --> 00:52:39,721
SO, WHAT HAPPENED?

967
00:52:39,787 --> 00:52:40,755
WITH WHAT?

968
00:52:40,822 --> 00:52:41,990
ELISE.

969
00:52:42,056 --> 00:52:43,391
[ CHUCKLING ]

970
00:52:43,458 --> 00:52:44,759
WELL, YOU KNOW.

971
00:52:44,826 --> 00:52:45,860
NO.

972
00:52:47,228 --> 00:52:49,430
WELL, IT STARTED SLOWLY

973
00:52:49,497 --> 00:52:52,400
AND...ENDED NICE.

974
00:52:52,467 --> 00:52:54,902
"NICE"?
WHAT THE FUCK IS "NICE"?

975
00:52:54,969 --> 00:52:56,137
DID YOU BANG HER?

976
00:52:56,204 --> 00:52:58,239
[ Chuckling ] NO.

977
00:52:58,306 --> 00:52:59,507
YOU DOG!

978
00:52:59,574 --> 00:53:01,943
YOU FLEA-INFESTED HOUND,
YOU BANGED HER.

979
00:53:04,379 --> 00:53:06,147
DETAILS.
I WANT DETAILS.

980
00:53:06,214 --> 00:53:07,548
JUST DON'T KISS AND TELL.

981
00:53:07,615 --> 00:53:10,118
GUESS WHAT?
OUR BOY FINALLY GOT LAID.

982
00:53:10,184 --> 00:53:11,953
[ LAUGHING ]

983
00:53:12,020 --> 00:53:13,454
HE CALLED!

984
00:53:13,521 --> 00:53:16,491
MY FATHER!
HE CALLED ME.

985
00:53:16,557 --> 00:53:17,759
HE WANTS TO HAVE DINNER.

986
00:53:17,825 --> 00:53:20,995
HE SAID, UH...
HE SAID HE MISSED ME.

987
00:53:26,901 --> 00:53:28,670
[ SQUEALS ]

988
00:53:35,576 --> 00:53:39,347
[ SIZZLING ]

989
00:53:39,414 --> 00:53:42,183
THIS IS GOING TO BE
SO GREAT.

990
00:53:42,250 --> 00:53:43,518
YOU AND ELISE WILL DATE,

991
00:53:43,584 --> 00:53:45,486
AND WE WILL DOUBLE-DATE.

992
00:53:45,553 --> 00:53:47,555
AND YEARS FROM NOW,

993
00:53:47,622 --> 00:53:49,190
THE TWO OF YOU
WILL FALL IN LOVE

994
00:53:49,257 --> 00:53:50,558
AND GET MARRIED,

995
00:53:50,625 --> 00:53:52,460
AND YOU'LL COME OVER
TO OUR HOUSE,

996
00:53:52,527 --> 00:53:55,830
WHERE YOU WILL LEAVE
YOUR KIDS WITH US
AND THE BABYSITTER

997
00:53:55,897 --> 00:53:57,699
WHILE THE FOUR OF US
GET CHINESE FOOD.

998
00:54:00,001 --> 00:54:00,935
HEY, DAVID...

999
00:54:01,002 --> 00:54:03,237
TAKE OVER FOR ME HERE,
WILL YOU?

1000
00:54:03,304 --> 00:54:04,305
YEAH.

1001
00:54:04,372 --> 00:54:05,606
SOMETHING I SAID?

1002
00:54:05,673 --> 00:54:07,408
[ CHUCKLES ] NO.

1003
00:54:07,475 --> 00:54:09,210
I'M JUST GONNA GO GET
SOME BEER, OKAY?

1004
00:54:09,277 --> 00:54:10,645
YOU'RE GOOD.

1005
00:54:10,712 --> 00:54:11,746
YEAH.

1006
00:54:11,813 --> 00:54:15,917
"KILL BRONTOSAURUS,
GET BEER, COME BACK."

1007
00:54:15,983 --> 00:54:17,385
SEE YA.

1008
00:54:17,452 --> 00:54:18,586
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

1009
00:54:18,653 --> 00:54:19,987
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1010
00:54:21,222 --> 00:54:22,457
[ PLATES RATTLING ]

1011
00:54:22,523 --> 00:54:24,158
I THINK I'VE PUSHED HIM
TOO HARD.

1012
00:54:27,161 --> 00:54:30,164
I ASKED HIM TO COME
WITH ME TO, UH...

1013
00:54:30,231 --> 00:54:33,434
HAVE DINNER WITH MY FATHER
TOMORROW NIGHT AND...

1014
00:54:35,269 --> 00:54:38,573
I COULD JUST SEE THE PANIC
IN HIS EYES.
LOOK, I'LL GO
TALK TO HIM.

1015
00:54:38,639 --> 00:54:42,076
I'LL GO TALK TO HIM.
OKAY?

1016
00:54:42,143 --> 00:54:43,778
YOU DON'T...HAVE TO.

1017
00:54:43,845 --> 00:54:45,012
IT'S FINE.

1018
00:54:47,482 --> 00:54:49,417
[ BIRDS CALLING ]

1019
00:54:51,753 --> 00:54:54,155
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

1020
00:54:57,058 --> 00:54:59,060
HEY.

1021
00:54:59,127 --> 00:55:00,728
HEY.

1022
00:55:00,795 --> 00:55:03,364
YOU JUST --
JUST DISAPPEARED.

1023
00:55:03,431 --> 00:55:05,833
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

1024
00:55:07,502 --> 00:55:09,437
SHE TOLD ME
ABOUT THE FATHER THING.

1025
00:55:10,905 --> 00:55:14,108
WHY DON'T I JUST GO,
YOU KNOW?

1026
00:55:14,175 --> 00:55:16,043
I MEAN, IF IT'S
TOO MUCH FOR YOU.

1027
00:55:18,212 --> 00:55:19,480
YOU WOULD?

1028
00:55:20,448 --> 00:55:22,483
OF COURSE.

1029
00:55:22,550 --> 00:55:25,486
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
I GOT A...

1030
00:55:25,553 --> 00:55:26,621
I GOT A DATE WITH ELISE,

1031
00:55:26,687 --> 00:55:29,157
BUT...I'LL JUST
RESCHEDULE.

1032
00:55:32,593 --> 00:55:34,228
I'M NOT GONNA
FUCK THIS UP, DAVID.

1033
00:55:36,531 --> 00:55:37,865
JUST NOT.

1034
00:55:40,034 --> 00:55:41,502
SO DON'T.

1035
00:55:45,273 --> 00:55:46,908
[ CHUCKLES ]

1036
00:55:53,981 --> 00:55:55,016
ALL SET?

1037
00:55:55,082 --> 00:55:55,983
HMM.

1038
00:55:56,050 --> 00:55:58,619
HEY!
[ RAPID FOOTSTEPS ]

1039
00:55:58,686 --> 00:55:59,720
HEY.
HEY.

1040
00:55:59,787 --> 00:56:01,022
I'M GLAD I CAUGHT YOU.

1041
00:56:01,088 --> 00:56:03,825
I DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO LEAVE WITHOUT...

1042
00:56:05,760 --> 00:56:06,894
THIS IS FOOFUR.

1043
00:56:06,961 --> 00:56:08,763
[ SIGHS ]
[ GIGGLES ]

1044
00:56:08,830 --> 00:56:11,032
IT'S FROM WHEN
I WAS A KID.

1045
00:56:16,938 --> 00:56:18,206
Good luck.

1046
00:56:20,141 --> 00:56:22,977
SEE YA, DAVID.

1047
00:56:23,044 --> 00:56:25,046
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]
YOU READY TO ROLL?

1048
00:56:27,982 --> 00:56:29,050
OKAY.

1049
00:56:30,418 --> 00:56:33,221
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

1050
00:56:39,727 --> 00:56:43,664
[ RADIO CLICKS ]
Bell Biv DeVoe:
♪ AHH, OOH, YEAH ♪

1051
00:56:43,731 --> 00:56:45,199
♪ DO ME, BABY ♪

1052
00:56:45,266 --> 00:56:47,935
♪ I LIKE IT
IN THE MORNING TIME, YEAH ♪

1053
00:56:48,002 --> 00:56:52,306
♪ DO ME, BABY ♪
♪ SOMETIMES I LOVE IT
IN THE EVENING, TOO, BABY ♪

1054
00:56:52,373 --> 00:56:54,075
♪ DO ME, BABY ♪
♪ DO ME, BABY ♪

1055
00:56:54,141 --> 00:56:56,944
♪ CAN YOU DO ME ALL OVER,
YEAH, YEAH, BABY? ♪

1056
00:56:57,011 --> 00:56:58,913
♪ DO ME, BABY ♪
♪ DO ME, BABY ♪

1057
00:56:58,980 --> 00:57:00,882
COME ON.

1058
00:57:00,948 --> 00:57:04,452
Bell Biv DeVoe and David:
♪ THE TIME WAS 6 O'CLOCK
ON THE SWATCH WATCH ♪

1059
00:57:04,518 --> 00:57:07,088
♪ NO TIME TO CHILL,
GOT A DATE, CAN'T BE LATE ♪

1060
00:57:07,154 --> 00:57:09,490
♪ HEY, THE GIRL
IS GONNA DO ME ♪

1061
00:57:09,557 --> 00:57:10,758
YOU'RE SUCH A LOSER!

1062
00:57:10,825 --> 00:57:12,660
♪ MOVE TO THE JACUZZI ♪

1063
00:57:12,727 --> 00:57:14,195
All: ♪ OOH, THAT BOOTY ♪

1064
00:57:14,262 --> 00:57:17,899
♪ SMACK IT UP, FLIP IT,
RUB IT DOWN, OH, NO! ♪

1065
00:57:17,965 --> 00:57:20,868
♪ DO ME, BABY ♪
♪ DO ME, JENNY ♪

1066
00:57:20,935 --> 00:57:22,803
Bell Biv DeVoe: ♪ YEAH... ♪

1067
00:57:22,870 --> 00:57:25,973
[ LAUGHING ]
♪ DO ME, JENNY ♪

1068
00:57:26,040 --> 00:57:27,942
♪ OH, BABY,
I LIKE IT JUST LIKE THAT ♪

1069
00:57:28,009 --> 00:57:29,677
♪ DO ME, JENNY! ♪

1070
00:57:29,744 --> 00:57:32,413
♪ AND I LOVE THE WAY YOU DO IT
TO ME, BABY, YEAH ♪

1071
00:57:32,480 --> 00:57:33,981
♪ DO ME, JENNY ♪

1072
00:57:34,048 --> 00:57:36,450
♪ OH, MOVE JUST
A LITTLE BIT CLOSER ♪

1073
00:57:36,517 --> 00:57:40,288
♪ YOU CAN DO ME IN THE MORNING,
YOU CAN DO ME IN THE NIGHT ♪

1074
00:57:40,354 --> 00:57:43,057
♪ YOU CAN DO ME
WHEN YOU WANNA DO ME ♪♪

1075
00:57:43,124 --> 00:57:46,093
[ DISTANT,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

1076
00:58:02,209 --> 00:58:04,078
[ DAVID GRAY'S "SAIL AWAY"
PLAYS ]

1077
00:58:05,579 --> 00:58:07,615
LET ME CHECK
MY MACHINE AGAIN.

1078
00:58:07,682 --> 00:58:09,483
JEN...

1079
00:58:09,550 --> 00:58:11,619
YOU JUST DID THAT.

1080
00:58:13,921 --> 00:58:19,593
♪ COLD WALL FEELS HARD ♪

1081
00:58:19,660 --> 00:58:23,397
♪ YOU REST IN MY HEART ♪

1082
00:58:25,599 --> 00:58:31,105
♪ TOO LONG STOOD STILL ♪

1083
00:58:31,172 --> 00:58:34,342
♪ HEART BEATS FOR YOUR... ♪

1084
00:58:34,408 --> 00:58:35,776
[ KEY CLICKS, ENGINE STOPS ]

1085
00:58:35,843 --> 00:58:39,347
♪ I'LL THINK ABOUT YOU ♪

1086
00:58:39,413 --> 00:58:42,383
♪ SOMETIME ♪♪

1087
00:58:42,450 --> 00:58:43,751
THANKS FOR COMING.

1088
00:58:43,818 --> 00:58:45,252
OF COURSE.

1089
00:58:46,654 --> 00:58:48,089
I'M SO SORRY, JEN.

1090
00:58:50,758 --> 00:58:52,293
I KNOW.

1091
00:59:01,168 --> 00:59:03,104
[ CRIES ]

1092
00:59:21,555 --> 00:59:23,958
DAVID! DAVID...

1093
00:59:24,025 --> 00:59:25,526
SORRY.

1094
00:59:25,593 --> 00:59:26,660
SORRY. I-I JUST...

1095
00:59:26,727 --> 00:59:28,796
WHAT WAS THAT?

1096
00:59:28,863 --> 00:59:30,097
I'M SORRY.

1097
00:59:30,164 --> 00:59:31,265
I-I-I JUST...

1098
00:59:31,332 --> 00:59:32,299
I-I THOUGHT...

1099
00:59:32,366 --> 00:59:34,268
IS THAT WHAT THIS
IS REALLY ABOUT?

1100
00:59:34,335 --> 00:59:35,403
HUH?

1101
00:59:35,469 --> 00:59:38,005
"HELP JENNY OUT. MAYBE
SHE'LL FINALLY FUCK ME!"

1102
00:59:38,072 --> 00:59:40,441
NO! O-OF COURSE NOT.
I-I WAS --

1103
00:59:40,508 --> 00:59:43,677
WHAT'S IT GONNA
TAKE FOR US TO GET
THIS STRAIGHT, HUH?

1104
00:59:43,744 --> 00:59:44,912
HUH?!

1105
00:59:44,979 --> 00:59:48,883
JESUS CHRIST, JENNY.

1106
00:59:48,949 --> 00:59:50,885
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1107
00:59:50,951 --> 00:59:53,220
WOULD YOU JUST HOLD ON
A SECOND, PLEASE?

1108
00:59:55,022 --> 00:59:56,490
JEN...

1109
00:59:58,592 --> 01:00:00,928
JENNY, PLEASE, JUST
GIVE ME A CHANCE TO EXPL--

1110
01:00:00,995 --> 01:00:02,897
[ DOOR HINGES CREAKS ]
FUCK OFF, DAVID.

1111
01:00:06,100 --> 01:00:09,203
[ BOTH MOANING,
BREATHING HEAVILY ]

1112
01:00:24,718 --> 01:00:26,353
JENNY!

1113
01:00:26,420 --> 01:00:28,122
JENNY...

1114
01:00:28,189 --> 01:00:29,457
JENNY!

1115
01:00:29,523 --> 01:00:30,858
JENNY!

1116
01:00:31,592 --> 01:00:32,626
JENNY!

1117
01:00:32,693 --> 01:00:34,728
DAVID, STOP HER!
JENNY!

1118
01:00:34,795 --> 01:00:35,863
I'M SORRY!

1119
01:00:35,930 --> 01:00:38,499
[ DOOR SLAMS CLOSED ]

1120
01:00:38,566 --> 01:00:40,568
[ CAR DOORS OPEN, CLOSE ]

1121
01:00:40,634 --> 01:00:42,937
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

1122
01:00:43,003 --> 01:00:44,638
[ CAR DEPARTS ]

1123
01:00:44,705 --> 01:00:46,841
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

1124
01:00:48,742 --> 01:00:49,877
FUCK!

1125
01:00:49,944 --> 01:00:51,912
[ MUTTERING ]

1126
01:00:51,979 --> 01:00:53,114
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

1127
01:00:53,180 --> 01:00:54,748
GET THE FUCK AWAY
FROM ME.

1128
01:00:54,815 --> 01:00:57,118
Jenny: NO! NO! NO!

1129
01:00:57,184 --> 01:00:59,220
NO! NO!

1130
01:00:59,286 --> 01:01:00,488
NO!

1131
01:01:00,554 --> 01:01:02,690
DON'T BE FUCKING STUPID!
GET UP!

1132
01:01:02,757 --> 01:01:05,793
GET UP!
WHAT ARE YOU --
JEN, DON'T THROW THE CHAIR.

1133
01:01:05,860 --> 01:01:08,295
I WANT IT ALL GONE!

1134
01:01:08,362 --> 01:01:11,365
ALL OF IT --
EVERYTHING HE EVER TOUCHED,

1135
01:01:11,432 --> 01:01:15,436
EVERYTHING
HE EVER LOOKED AT --
I WANT IT ALL GONE!

1136
01:01:15,503 --> 01:01:16,804
[ GLASS SHATTERING ]

1137
01:01:16,871 --> 01:01:19,340
AGH!

1138
01:01:19,406 --> 01:01:22,143
THERE IS NO...ONE.

1139
01:01:22,209 --> 01:01:23,611
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ]

1140
01:01:23,677 --> 01:01:25,880
[ SHATTERING CONTINUES ]

1141
01:01:29,116 --> 01:01:30,918
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]
Alan: JEN!

1142
01:01:30,985 --> 01:01:33,721
JEN, WILL YOU OPEN
THE DOOR?!

1143
01:01:33,788 --> 01:01:36,090
I JUST WANT TO TALK!

1144
01:01:36,157 --> 01:01:39,660
COME ON, IT'S BEEN A WEEK!
I KNOW YOU'RE THERE!

1145
01:01:39,727 --> 01:01:42,696
YOU CAN'T AVOID ME FOREVER.

1146
01:01:42,763 --> 01:01:44,431
I JUST WANT TO FUCKING EXPLAIN.

1147
01:01:44,498 --> 01:01:47,635
WILL YOU COME DOWN
TO THE FUCKING DOOR?!

1148
01:01:47,701 --> 01:01:49,503
[ CAT SCREECHES ]

1149
01:01:49,570 --> 01:01:51,539
FUCK!

1150
01:01:51,605 --> 01:01:53,073
[ In distance ] FUCK!

1151
01:02:00,948 --> 01:02:02,683
JENNY, I NEED TO TALK
TO YOU.

1152
01:02:02,750 --> 01:02:03,851
[ THUD ]

1153
01:02:03,918 --> 01:02:06,654
GET AWAY FROM ME!

1154
01:02:06,720 --> 01:02:09,557
JUST GIVE ME
FIVE MINUTES.
WHO DO YOU THINK
YOU ARE?!

1155
01:02:09,623 --> 01:02:10,791
YOU WALK ALL OVER ME,

1156
01:02:10,858 --> 01:02:12,092
YOU STALK ME, AND
YOU STILL DON'T KNOW

1157
01:02:12,159 --> 01:02:13,561
WHY I DON'T
WANT TO SEE YOU?!

1158
01:02:13,627 --> 01:02:15,763
GO AWAY, ALAN.
DAVID,
STAY OUT OF THIS.

1159
01:02:15,829 --> 01:02:18,032
NO, SHE DOESN'T WANT
TO TALK TO YOU, MAN.
SO TAKE A FUCKING HIKE!

1160
01:02:18,098 --> 01:02:20,467
JUST LET FUCKING GO!

1161
01:02:24,038 --> 01:02:25,839
[ GRUNTS SOFTLY ]

1162
01:02:25,906 --> 01:02:27,842
THE FUCK!

1163
01:02:27,908 --> 01:02:30,444
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]
I'M SORRY, MAN.

1164
01:02:30,511 --> 01:02:32,146
UGH!

1165
01:02:33,614 --> 01:02:34,915
[ PANTING ]

1166
01:02:34,982 --> 01:02:37,117
[ PANTING ]

1167
01:02:43,023 --> 01:02:44,491
DAVID?

1168
01:02:49,463 --> 01:02:50,564
I FUCKED UP.

1169
01:02:51,732 --> 01:02:53,033
I KNOW THAT.

1170
01:02:58,472 --> 01:03:00,307
I JUST WANTED
MY CHANCE TO EXPLAIN.

1171
01:03:10,651 --> 01:03:13,587
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

1172
01:03:25,299 --> 01:03:27,434
WHO DOES HE THINK
HE IS?

1173
01:03:39,546 --> 01:03:40,681
[ GASPS ]

1174
01:03:42,249 --> 01:03:44,652
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

1175
01:03:49,623 --> 01:03:51,492
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

1176
01:03:54,895 --> 01:03:56,230
WHAT'S UP?

1177
01:03:58,465 --> 01:04:00,301
THIS CAME THROUGH
MY WINDOW.

1178
01:04:03,704 --> 01:04:05,039
[ SIGHS ]

1179
01:04:05,105 --> 01:04:07,107
WHAT THE FUCK
IS HIS PROBLEM?

1180
01:04:15,082 --> 01:04:16,116
[ Sobbing ] CAN I STAY?

1181
01:04:16,183 --> 01:04:18,218
YEAH, COME IN.

1182
01:04:18,285 --> 01:04:20,154
I GOTTA MAKE HIM STOP.

1183
01:04:21,755 --> 01:04:23,891
Man: [ On police radio ]
YEAH, COPY THAT. THIS IS 1027.

1184
01:04:23,958 --> 01:04:27,428
[ SIREN WAILS ]

1185
01:04:27,494 --> 01:04:28,495
SHIT.

1186
01:04:28,562 --> 01:04:32,066
ALAN!

1187
01:04:32,132 --> 01:04:33,801
WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON, MAN?

1188
01:04:33,867 --> 01:04:35,936
I THINK THIS TIP WAS HOT.
WE'VE SEIZED NARCOTICS.

1189
01:04:36,003 --> 01:04:38,639
WE ARE NOW APPREHENDING
THE SUSPECT AND TAKING HIM
DOWNTOWN.

1190
01:04:38,706 --> 01:04:40,474
OH, SHIT.

1191
01:04:40,541 --> 01:04:42,076
OH, SHIT.

1192
01:04:44,378 --> 01:04:46,647
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

1193
01:04:50,818 --> 01:04:52,019
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

1194
01:04:52,086 --> 01:04:53,587
[ SIREN CHIRPS ]

1195
01:04:55,856 --> 01:04:57,257
[ DOOR OPENS ]

1196
01:04:57,324 --> 01:04:58,525
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

1197
01:04:58,592 --> 01:05:00,094
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1198
01:05:02,029 --> 01:05:04,398
[ Panting ]
THEY ARRESTED ALAN.

1199
01:05:08,068 --> 01:05:10,104
THERE WERE POLICE

1200
01:05:10,170 --> 01:05:13,173
THEY WERE COMING OUT
OF HIS HOUSE

1201
01:05:13,240 --> 01:05:15,542
THEY FOUND THE DRUGS.

1202
01:05:21,048 --> 01:05:22,282
JEN?

1203
01:05:23,584 --> 01:05:24,651
WHAT?

1204
01:05:26,954 --> 01:05:28,589
I THOUGHT...

1205
01:05:30,891 --> 01:05:32,526
I GUESS HE'S GONE, HUH?

1206
01:05:43,704 --> 01:05:45,105
JEN?

1207
01:05:48,509 --> 01:05:51,245
[ INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

1208
01:06:38,258 --> 01:06:40,060
David: AND THAT WAS IT.

1209
01:06:40,127 --> 01:06:42,796
I THINK HE SERVED 18 MONTHS.

1210
01:06:42,863 --> 01:06:45,098
AFTER HE GOT OUT,
I HAD HEARD A LOT OF RUMORS --

1211
01:06:45,165 --> 01:06:48,302
HEARD HE WAS INSTITUTIONALIZED
FOR A SHORT TIME,

1212
01:06:48,368 --> 01:06:50,471
DOING A LOT OF DRUGS.

1213
01:06:50,537 --> 01:06:52,439
WHO KNOWS, REALLY?

1214
01:06:52,506 --> 01:06:54,274
AFTER GRADUATION,
WE MOVED TO THE CITY,

1215
01:06:54,341 --> 01:06:58,145
GOT AN UNLISTED PHONE NUMBER,
TRIED TO GET ON WITH OUR LIVES.

1216
01:07:00,080 --> 01:07:01,682
SOMEHOW HE FOUND US.

1217
01:07:05,352 --> 01:07:07,254
WE FOUND THEM.
WE FOUND THEM.

1218
01:07:07,321 --> 01:07:08,856
GET ME AN AMBULANCE
DOWN HERE.

1219
01:07:08,922 --> 01:07:10,557
I don't know if they're dead or
alive.

1220
01:07:10,624 --> 01:07:12,693
Somebody get me
an ambulance right now!

1221
01:07:14,194 --> 01:07:15,462
STAND UP.

1222
01:07:15,529 --> 01:07:17,197
COME ON, STAND UP.

1223
01:07:17,264 --> 01:07:20,133
Woman: [ On P.A. ] DR. JONES,
YOU ARE NEEDED IN THE E.R.

1224
01:07:20,200 --> 01:07:22,102
COME ON.
[ Grunting ] ALL RIGHT.

1225
01:07:22,169 --> 01:07:23,737
COME ON.

1226
01:07:23,804 --> 01:07:25,973
OW! OW!

1227
01:07:26,039 --> 01:07:27,541
